Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.21,0:00:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to just conclude, and then a few remarks about why addictive persons react the way they do to any threat to their addiction.\NYou can see now, if happiness is something that lies outside of you, and if you've given the power over your life to that out there,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.68,0:00:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,you can now see why you react the way you react to any threat to that, what you now believe to be the source.\NWhether it's a relationship, that person might leave my life, the terror at that, I might lose my job.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.82,0:00:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see why people now react the way they react, and in knowing that, you know much better how to handle them.\NA person here, if you tell them they cannot drink anymore, if you put them in a hospital, if you pull them into treatment, will go into grief.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.81,0:00:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the mourning and the depression about?\NIt's not because of the loss of alcohol for your life, it's because you're cut off from this state,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.87,0:00:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and the feeling that...\NWell, one will never more experience that state.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.13,0:01:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The state of apathy and hopelessness that almost led to suicide came out of the conviction that I am now and forever cut off from any access to this state.\NNot from alcohol.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.05,0:01:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,By that time, alcohol made me throw up, you know?\NHalf an ounce of it had a violent and terrible negative effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.56,0:01:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I hated it, and I detested it.\NSo it wasn't grief and mourning over the loss of alcohol.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.24,0:01:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It was grief and mourning for the same reason that the person...\Nin Lost Horizon is in grief and mourning over the loss of that state.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.18,0:01:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why you go into fear.\NAny threat to your supply, then, is not the fear of the loss of the drug.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.22,0:01:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the fear of the loss of this state, that you will have to live on this planet forever, the terror,\Nthat you will never again experience a connection with that which is real, because it's their connection.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.04,0:01:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Another name for what's on top of the board is reality.\NYou will never experience...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.76,0:02:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is real again.\NYou will always be in the plastic world of the solar plexus and the foreverness-chasing of the forms of all that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.93,0:02:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The desiringness is obvious.\NThat's part and parcel of the entrapment.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.15,0:02:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The anger.\NIf you stand between a person and his source of supply, he may well kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.61,0:02:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And it does happen, because you are cutting him off from God.\NIt's really what you are doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.29,0:02:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,His experience of that which is his own godness, his own higher selfness,\Nand...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.77,0:02:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,people.\NPeople will, of course, go into a rage.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.77,0:02:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So now you see the reactions to when we threaten a person's addiction.\NWhen you call him to question, when you say,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.13,0:02:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,George, don't you think you're drinking too much?\NLook what you're bringing up in him.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.86,0:02:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You see what you're bringing up in him?\NAll of his survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.54,0:02:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You think you're experiencing God too much?\NIt's really what you're saying to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.70,0:02:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what you're saying to him.\NSo what you're implying now is a threat of his connection.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.08,0:03:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So when we get through talking today,\NI'm sure you'll see a much different way,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.32,0:03:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,of holding the situation,\Nand therefore how to approach the person,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.06,0:03:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,so that they don't go into a panic over loss, or a rage,\Nor end up hating you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.48,0:03:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,They will divorce you, you know?\NIf you threaten their supply,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.50,0:03:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,they'll say, well, you and I are not getting along,\Nand I'll have to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.98,0:03:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,They will leave out of anger, out of fear,\Nof the loss of their supply.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.08,0:03:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Any threat.\NSo I just wanted to clear that up,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.27,0:03:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,of why people react the way they do to the loss.\NWhat the loss is that they're feeling threatened.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.53,0:03:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not the drug, and it's not the alcohol.\NYou see, after a while, a person doesn't care what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.83,0:03:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,as long as it accesses this energy state.\NYou see, the psychological explanations of addiction
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.66,0:03:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,don't hold water clinically and experientially.\NThe psychological explanation is that they're running away
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.94,0:03:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,from reality, that the person drinks because they\Nare trying to escape their fears, their anxieties,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.04,0:04:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,their angers, their resentments.\NThorazine will get rid of your anxiety for a couple weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.76,0:04:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,One good shot of Thorazine, and you won't feel nervous,\Nuntil probably Christmas time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.87,0:04:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Antidepressants will get rid of your depressions.\NA combination of the two will get rid of your anxiety
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.15,0:04:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and your depression.\NPharmacologically, I did that for 30 years as a psychiatrist.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.71,0:04:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I got rid of people with psychopharmacology.\NBut nobody ever calls you for a refill.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.43,0:04:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody ever says, Doc, my prescription\Nfor antidepressants and Thorazine went down the toilet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.59,0:04:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,With Percodan, it always goes down the toilet, doesn't it?\NDoc?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.45,0:04:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,My four-year-old daughter ate the prescription\Nfor Percodan and got thrown out with her diapers
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.95,0:04:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,because you gave me a repeat.\NNobody asked for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.19,0:04:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The elimination of these negatives\Nis not what is sought.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.85,0:04:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, these are born willingly\Nin order to access this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.64,0:04:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Because as the addiction goes on,\Nthe experience of these higher states
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.18,0:05:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes briefer and briefer.\NAnd they're followed by prolonged states of agony.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.86,0:05:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And the person is actually willing and will accept.\NThat this is going to bring them prolonged agony,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.98,0:05:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,even for a few moments of that experience.\NAnd people will tell you when they come back into the program
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.48,0:05:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,who've been out,\NI knew it wasn't going to last more than a couple of minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.98,0:05:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But I just had to, what?\NReconnect with that experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.48,0:05:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,At whatever the cost.\NSo it isn't the running away and people will say,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.12,0:05:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't drink to escape from life.\NI drank so that I could enjoy it more.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.12,0:05:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So that I could be more with life.\NI didn't drink so I could avoid going to the party.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.12,0:05:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I went so that I could go to the party\Nand be more with life.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.12,0:05:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,More with the party than I would have been\Nhad I been in my normal state.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.12,0:05:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,See, that which is sought now begins to explain\Nreally what's going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.82,0:05:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,These energy states are,\Nthese fields of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.92,0:05:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,as I said, are impersonal.\NAnd they totally dominate how we experience life
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.40,0:05:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and how we experience the world.\NSo we did one column over here
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.40,0:06:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,called Brain Chemistry.\NWe can put columns all the way across the board.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.40,0:06:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're going to start marching across the board now.\NAnd we'll put here the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.72,0:06:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,How do these energy fields,\Nsee these energy fields are so powerful
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.74,0:06:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,that they literally have control\Nover what happens in your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.74,0:06:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of what you're holding in mind.\NSee the difficulty in people and consciousness work
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.44,0:06:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is to be able to grasp what is the power of mind.\NThat it is so all powerful that they can't even get
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.44,0:06:41.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that it has power.\NThe energy field is so powerful that it literally
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.37,0:06:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,controls your perceptions.\NIt controls the experiences that comes into your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.63,0:06:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You might look at this energy field as a grid,\Nan energy grid.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.82,0:06:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,This grid then\Ncreates and controls what goes in and out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.92,0:07:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So that a person,\Nin this state of apathy, let us say,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.08,0:07:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,state of apathy,\Nwhen they look at the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.62,0:07:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,what do they literally see?\NWhat kind of a world do they experience?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.87,0:07:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,They experience a world of hopelessness.\NI can't even read that myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.48,0:07:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how you can.\NHopelessness.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.48,0:07:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I must be into apathy about my handwriting.\NI just got that, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.48,0:07:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Hopelessness.\NAs you see, it is not hopeless.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.88,0:07:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's legible.\NBut anyway, the energy field of apathy
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.88,0:07:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,creates a perceptual field\Nand an experiential
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.88,0:07:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,field in which what you see\Nis hopelessness in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.95,0:07:49.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything you look at is hopeless.\NYou open the paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.95,0:07:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It talks about an international situation\Nwith so-and-so, and you say,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.95,0:07:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,well, that's hopeless.\NIt talks about world hunger, let's say.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.24,0:08:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's hopeless.\NHunger has always been with mankind,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.24,0:08:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,so it's hopeless.\NI mean, the mind will always find
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.24,0:08:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,intellectual rationalization to justify\Nthe position of the energy field.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.24,0:08:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,This relationship is hopeless.\NYou know?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.24,0:08:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,My sister-in-law and her husband,\Nit's hopeless, that marriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.24,0:08:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So you begin to see hopelessness everywhere.\NAnd because you're holding hopelessness,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.24,0:08:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,it brings into your life\Nthe experience of hopelessness.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.24,0:08:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,If you think it's hopeless that you can train your dog,\Nyou know, to do it outside,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.39,0:08:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,you can be sure that\Nif you're holding that this dog is hopeless,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.39,0:08:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,then you're never going to get him to the train\Nbecause you are holding a powerful energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.39,0:08:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that says he is hopeless.\NThe dog is coming from a much less powerful energy field,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.28,0:08:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and he will just go with your hopelessness\Nand do it on the rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.28,0:08:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So, from the most mundane\Nto the most profoundly spiritual levels, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.28,0:08:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,our energy fields are dominated by that\Nwhich we're holding in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.28,0:09:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Our relationships, you know, reflect that.\NAt this level down here of guilt,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.86,0:09:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,we start going into the hells,\Nthe hells going from there on down,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.86,0:09:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,in which life seems to be an endless source of pain.\NSo, coming out of guilt, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.99,0:09:15.99,Default,,0,0,0,,we have the world of pain,\Nsee, at the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.99,0:09:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we have the world of hopelessness.\NIt's hopeless that the pain is going to be inevitable
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.18,0:09:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,because from this level,\Npain is part and parcel of all of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.18,0:09:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,all of experiences accompanied by pain.\NThe next higher levels,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.82,0:09:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,this is a sad world, see?\NThe world of grief,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.43,0:09:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,it is a sad world.\NSo, the person in hopelessness walks down the street
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.13,0:09:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and sees the hopelessness of society,\Nhopelessness of civilization,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.13,0:09:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,hopelessness of man,\Nhopelessness of man's condition,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.13,0:09:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,hopelessness.\NThis person, instead, sees sadness.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.20,0:09:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in walking down the street,\Nthe person sees the children
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.20,0:10:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and how sad that is,\Nknowing the pain that they're going to go through
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.20,0:10:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,as they grow up, etc.\NYou know?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.36,0:10:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The sadness, they look at the old people and say,\Nisn't that sad, the old people?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.36,0:10:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I was at a restaurant in Sedona\None time when that happened, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.36,0:10:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I was looking at some people at the next table\Nand they looked to me like they were in a state of bliss,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.36,0:10:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,they were all in a state of total oneness.\NI mean, they were so connected
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.36,0:10:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and had known each other for so long\Nand nothing needed to be said,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.36,0:10:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,they just sat there blissed out with each other, you know?\NJust so happy to be in each other's presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.36,0:10:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And the person with me said,\Nlook at those old people, isn't that sad?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.36,0:10:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that sad? What was sad?\NI don't know, I couldn't see anything to be sad about.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.36,0:10:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Apparently, the person was referring to\Nwhat they're projecting onto the situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.36,0:10:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no sadness there.\NBut when you open the paper,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.90,0:10:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,there is much, if you are into sadness,\Nto be sad about, is that not so?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.90,0:10:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,There is much to be hopeless about,\Nif that is where you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.90,0:10:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,There is nothing but sin.\NIf you are into a refueled of 30,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.90,0:11:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,in which the world of pain is the world of sin,\Nyou see page after page of sin, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.90,0:11:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Sin and wrong, being wrong.\NAs you move up, you move into,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.41,0:11:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,out of the sad world,\Nyou move up into the fearful world.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.41,0:11:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is the world of fearfulness,\Nof course, everybody is familiar with,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.54,0:11:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,from robbers, to muggers, to rapers,\Nto the IRS, to God knows what,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.54,0:11:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,what people think of you, people's opinion,\Nwhether you'll be well, help, wealth,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.54,0:11:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,all the endless fears,\Nand the enormous amount of human energy
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.57,0:11:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that goes in to then defend themselves\Nagainst these fears.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.08,0:11:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, a typical apartment in New York City\Nhas six locks, and then it has
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.08,0:11:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,L-shaped crowbars around it,\Nand then it has alarm systems,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.08,0:11:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and then it has bars in the windows.\NAnd when you go out, you may well get mugged,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.08,0:11:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,is being held in mind.\NAnd I know people who have been mugged six times in a row,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.08,0:11:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and still living in the same high-rise apartment building.\NI've been mugged six times in this building.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.08,0:11:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I say, yes.\NAnd when are you moving?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.08,0:12:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'm not moving.\NWhy aren't you moving?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.08,0:12:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, how could I get a rent, you know, like that?\NHow could I get a rent like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.08,0:12:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see, there's the self-reinforcement,\Nthe self-reinforcement.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.08,0:12:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Although it's fearful, the person has,\Nan investment that this is a fearful world,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.08,0:12:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,because the investment in this being a fearful world\Nthen makes everything in their life meaningful.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.08,0:12:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,If they weren't living in a world of fear,\Nif they couldn't put that investment into the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.08,0:12:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,then none of their life would make sense,\Nbecause they're busy preparing for old age,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.12,0:12:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,incurring themselves with insurance,\Nand locking their doors,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.12,0:12:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and double-locking their cars,\Nand their whole life is one prevention
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.12,0:12:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,of the fearful happening in their life,\Nwhich, of course, makes it manifest.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.12,0:12:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Without the investment in fearfulness,\Nthen the life suddenly has no meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.56,0:12:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What is your whole life about now?\NJust like this person's investment is into
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.56,0:12:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,this is a sad world,\Nand if you try to take that away from them,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.56,0:12:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,now what is the context of their life?\NTheir whole life has been to prove
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.56,0:12:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that this is a sad place,\Nwhere you lose everything,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.56,0:13:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,where loved ones turn against you,\Nwhere bosses don't appreciate you,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.56,0:13:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,where those whom you invest with cheat on you, etc.\NTheir whole investment.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.56,0:13:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's an investment\Nthat's a secondary gain and a secondary payoff.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.56,0:13:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It merely reinforces it.\NIt's not really what sets the energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.56,0:13:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,as far as intention goes,\Nbut it's certainly the secondary payoff.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.56,0:13:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,In psychoanalysis that's called secondary payoff.\NThe secondary payoff reinforces the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.56,0:13:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see that which you set by your own intention\Nthen sets the energy of the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.12,0:13:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That field then determines what you see.\NNow you see why people move.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.56,0:13:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,They move so slowly in consciousness\Nbecause it's almost a deadlock,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.56,0:13:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and that which you think the world is\Nperceptually comes back to you as that,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.56,0:13:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,which reinforces your belief\Nthat that's the way the world is,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.66,0:14:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,which reinforces again\Nthat that's the kind of experiences that you have.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.40,0:14:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,This person here,\Nthis is a frustrating world.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.59,0:14:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Frustrating.\NThe person into that solar plexus wanting this,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.75,0:14:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,desiring this is never happy.\NThey're endlessly critical.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.75,0:14:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,They want everything to be different than the way it is.\NThe endless criticalness,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.75,0:14:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,the endless lack of satisfaction,\Nthe desiringness, the wantingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.75,0:14:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And now we can see why making more millions\Nactually is not very helpful.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.84,0:14:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,See?\NPeople who are dissatisfied,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.84,0:14:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,they're worth 50 million,\Nand that same dissatisfaction,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.32,0:14:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that wantingness,\Ninstead of saying,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.32,0:14:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,wow, I've got it made,\NI think I'll go and be happy
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.32,0:14:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and bliss out someplace.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.32,0:14:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The same energy that earned the first 50 million\Nnow drives them to earn more millions.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.32,0:14:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no end point.\NThere's no point at which the person can feel complete,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.32,0:14:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,satisfied, contented, happy.\NBecause happy,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.32,0:14:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,as we said,\Nhappiness is an energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.32,0:15:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that begins at around 500.\NDown here,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.36,0:15:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,what you get is satisfaction and pleasure.\NSo it's possible,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.45,0:15:10.45,Default,,0,0,0,,let's say in this energy field,\Nto get satisfaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.45,0:15:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You can plunge the dagger in your enemy's heart\Nand say,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.45,0:15:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,oh there,\Nbastard.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.45,0:15:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It feels good at the moment that you do it.\NYou see,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.45,0:15:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,you get pleasure\Nand you get satisfaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.45,0:15:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But that will not hold you up tomorrow morning.\NSo the person has to then go back in memory
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.45,0:15:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,to the satisfaction\Nand the person is then dependent on the memory
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.45,0:15:33.45,Default,,0,0,0,,of these past experiences\Nbecause the present reality
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.45,0:15:37.45,Default,,0,0,0,,is not the source of their happiness.\NThe awareness and consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.45,0:15:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,of the truth of who they are\Nand the present reality
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.45,0:15:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,is not the source of it.\NThe person in frustration then,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.16,0:15:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,you see,\Ndesiring this,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.51,0:15:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,as we said,\Nis seeking more and more.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.51,0:15:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But because they're on this energy level,\Nwe said that all that the world offers
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.51,0:15:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,is about 200,\Nall the money.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.51,0:16:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So 50 million will bring you\Na solar plexus,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.51,0:16:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,satisfaction,\Nand enjoyment
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.51,0:16:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,in which we calibrate.\NThe energy field of that is about 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.83,0:16:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you earn another 20 million,\Nyou will still have
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.83,0:16:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,energy experience of 200.\NSo more and more sex,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.83,0:16:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,going to bed with more and more people,\Nmore and more status symbols,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.83,0:16:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,more and more money\Nleads people who feel like that eventually
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.89,0:16:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,into suicide\Nand they become strange
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.89,0:16:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,when they get old\Nand they end up in the tabloids
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.89,0:16:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,with long fingernails and weirdness\Nand no one can understand
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.89,0:16:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,why with that many billions of dollars\Nthis person is not happy
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.89,0:16:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and instead they're paranoid,\Ntotally isolated from life
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.89,0:16:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and live a very wretched existence.\NThis eventually leads up to anger
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.21,0:16:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the frustration\Nand so we get a world of conflict.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.21,0:16:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We get the world of conflict.\NThe angry person sees
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.98,0:16:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,life as many wars\Nand competition.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.98,0:16:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is competition.\NDown here at the bottom of the box
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.68,0:17:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,everything is lose-lose.\NAt the bottom of the box,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.68,0:17:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody loses.\NAt the middle of the box,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.91,0:17:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,it's win-lose.\NIn the middle of the box then,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.42,0:17:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,if I win, you lose.\NAnd therefore relationships,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.74,0:17:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,business dealings,\Nall transactions
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.09,0:17:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,are held in a win-lose\Nproposition in the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.09,0:17:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Down here, everybody loses.\NIf I go back to live with the family,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.09,0:17:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,they all lose.\NThey're miserable.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.09,0:17:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm miserable.\NThey lose their TV set.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.09,0:17:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's lose-lose.\NDad's automobile insurance gets canceled
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.09,0:17:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,after racking it up again.\NSo it's lose-lose for everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.09,0:17:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,This is win-lose.\NAnd the angry person then sees
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.09,0:17:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,everything as conflict, competition\Nand they have to guard against that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.09,0:17:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's the chip on the shoulder\Nas one moves into pride and ownership.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.09,0:17:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,With pride goes, of course, ownership.\NAnd this is the world of status.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.16,0:18:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The world of status symbols.\NSee, this is all the same person
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.44,0:18:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,walking down the street.\NSee how differently,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.44,0:18:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean a different person\Nwalking down the same street.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.44,0:18:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,This one is seeing nothing but\Nthat which he hopes God will punish
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.92,0:18:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,for its sinfulness.\NThis one is seeing the hopelessness.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.92,0:18:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Hopeless.\NLook at those newspapers on the street.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.92,0:18:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at the dirt.\NLook at the poverty.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.92,0:18:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at the...\NThey're seeing hopelessness, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.92,0:18:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,This person is seeing the sadness of everything.\NThis person is scared as hell
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.92,0:18:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,walking down the street.\NThere's a mugger or a raper
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.92,0:18:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,or somebody out to get him every second.\NAnd of course they spot him, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.92,0:18:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,There's an old friend of mine\Nwho used to be a mugger
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.92,0:18:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,before he started teaching\Nthe Course in Miracles.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.92,0:18:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,He's now dead, God bless him,\NPaul Steinberg,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.76,0:18:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,who was the national coordinator\Nof the Course in Miracles.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.76,0:18:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And Betty Martin used to talk a lot.\NAnd he used to say,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.76,0:18:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,as a mugger,\Nthey just knew who was muggable.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.76,0:18:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They just stood in the doorway, he said.\NAnd the one that would walk by
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.76,0:19:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,furtively like that,\Nthey would instantly head for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.76,0:19:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They were very easy to knock over.\NSo the fearful, like, pull it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.76,0:19:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Pull that which they fear to them.\NSo the world of status, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.68,0:19:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the person is walking down the street\Nand they see your Gucci shoes,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.68,0:19:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,they get your Neiman Marcus handbag,\Nthey get your Saks Fifth Avenue sweater,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.68,0:19:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,they get your so-and-so hairdo,\Nthey get your so-and-so glasses,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.68,0:19:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,they get your, you know,\Neverything is status.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.68,0:19:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,They want you to get in your so-and-so car,\Nhopefully not dented,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.68,0:19:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,hopefully this is yours model.\NNot only that,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.68,0:19:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,but a Cadillac is not good enough.\NIt's one of the Cadillacs,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.68,0:19:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what I mean?\NI find out that there are various
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.68,0:19:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,gradations within Cadillac, right?\NYou find out about these things
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.92,0:19:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,if you look into them,\Nthat all these things
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.92,0:19:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,have gradations of status\Nwithin them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.72,0:19:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I always thought a Cadillac\Nwas something fantastic,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.72,0:19:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,but I found out it's\Nwhich Cadillac, not any of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.72,0:20:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,That attractiveness,\Nthat seductiveness of things
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.72,0:20:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,which we project onto it,\Nwhich doesn't exist
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.72,0:20:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,within the thing itself,\Nwhich Madison Avenue capitalizes on.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.11,0:20:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,See, when you smoke a cigarette,\Nthat doesn't mean you're going to be
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.20,0:20:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,riding across the horse\Nwith a 10-gallon hat
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.20,0:20:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and looking like Mr. Seductress,\Nyou know,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.20,0:20:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Movie Star.\NIt just means you're going to be
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.20,0:20:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,smoking a cigarette.\NThat's all it means.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.20,0:20:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You wear a certain perfume,\Nyou're going to smell good.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.20,0:20:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't mean that all the men\Nare going to fall down
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.20,0:20:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,like dominoes, does it?\NSo, this whole energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.20,0:20:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,this whole miasma,\Nthis charisma that is
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.20,0:20:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,spun around purposely.\NSo, the world of status, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.20,0:20:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,is very much that world\Nof all what we have projected
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.20,0:20:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,onto things, symbols,\Nbecause these things
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.20,0:20:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,are all only symbols\Nof taking care of that lack
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.20,0:20:50.49,Default,,0,0,0,,of inner self-esteem,\Nwhich, if we had,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.49,0:20:53.49,Default,,0,0,0,,all these things would be enjoyable\Nonly for what they are,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.49,0:20:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,but not for what our fantasy\Nadds onto them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.49,0:20:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,In the world,\Nwhat does the world become like
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.91,0:21:02.91,Default,,0,0,0,,at the level of courage, then?\NWhat does the person
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.91,0:21:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,who is holding that energy field,\Ncoming from that space,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.91,0:21:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,how do they experience\Nthe same street?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.91,0:21:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the world like?\NIt's a fascinating challenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.91,0:21:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It's exciting, is it not?\NThis is a world of exciting opportunity,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.52,0:21:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,growth, challenge.\NPeople in that space
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.16,0:21:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,will say,\Nwell, I only got one life
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.16,0:21:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and I want to experience\Neverything there is to experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.16,0:21:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to learn\Nwhat there is to learn here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.16,0:21:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to learn\Nfrom my mistakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.16,0:21:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to learn\Nfrom my mistakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.64,0:21:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to face them,\Nhandle them,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.96,0:21:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,cope with them.\NWhatever it takes
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.96,0:21:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to handle this,\Nwhatever it takes
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.96,0:21:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,to overcome this,\NI want to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.05,0:21:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So, life is seen\Nas an exciting,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.05,0:21:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the world is an exciting challenge,\Nand the experience of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.05,0:21:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,then, is exhilarating.\NSo, a person in that energy level,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.08,0:21:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,\Nis excited to get up
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.08,0:21:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,in the morning\Nand see what is the challenge
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.08,0:21:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,of this day\Nand the empowerment
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.08,0:21:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that comes out of that.\NWhat happens
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.72,0:22:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,as you move up into neutral\Nis a world of okayness.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.85,0:22:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the world of okayness.\NThis is not a challenge anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.08,0:22:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay how it is.\NIt's okay if I get into college.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.08,0:22:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay if I don't.\NThere isn't any resistance now
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.08,0:22:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to how the world is.\NThe world is seen as okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.08,0:22:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,One is into neutral about it.\NIt's sort of a detachedness
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.62,0:22:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,or it could be a non-detachedness.\NTo how the world is,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.68,0:22:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,is all right.\NSo, there's a letting go
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.68,0:22:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,of resistance.\NThe benefit is
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.68,0:22:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the release of a lot of energy\Nthat was being held
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.68,0:22:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,in resistance down here,\Na lot of that resistance
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.68,0:22:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,is let go of.\NIt's okay the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.68,0:22:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the downside\Nof this energy field here
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.68,0:22:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,is flat.\NThe upside is okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.68,0:22:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The downside is flat.\NSo, people say,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.00,0:22:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,would you like to come to the party?\NWell, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.00,0:22:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay if you go to the party.\NIt's okay not.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.00,0:23:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So, very often you come across as flat.\NSo, there are people
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.06,0:23:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,who do a certain consciousness technique\Nthat they are not even aware of,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.06,0:23:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,but it dumps them into neutral.\NAnd a lot of them are described
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.06,0:23:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,by other members of the community\Nas flat.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.06,0:23:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll say,\Nyou know, these people are flat.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.06,0:23:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Please don't invite them.\NPlease don't invite them
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.06,0:23:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,because they are so flat.\NThe restaurants don't even like to see them
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.06,0:23:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,come in.\NBecause they are so flat.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.06,0:23:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay if they leave a tip\Nand it's okay if they don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.06,0:23:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So, they don't.\NSo, the waitresses don't like them.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.06,0:23:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The downside is egocentric flatness.\NThe upside is an okayness
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.06,0:23:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and a willingness to go along with.\NSo, its upside is that willingness
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.06,0:23:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,to go along with life\Nwithout resenting it,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.06,0:23:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,without resisting it,\Nwithout getting depressed about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.06,0:23:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,without being angry,\Nwithout being moralistic,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.06,0:23:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,without getting into right and wrong about it.\NSo, it is a move up
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.19,0:23:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,towards acceptance.\NAnd, of course, then we get,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.19,0:23:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,as we move into acceptance,\Nwe move into a world of harmony,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.19,0:24:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,a world of easygoingness,\Nand we move into an energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.19,0:24:06.21,Default,,0,0,0,,of cooperation.\NCompetitiveness comes in about 180.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.21,0:24:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Cooperation comes in about 400.\NSo, as we move into acceptance,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.21,0:24:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,we move into a world of togetherness,\Nof not togetherness
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.21,0:24:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,as Hollywood looks at it,\Nbut a togetherness in which
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.67,0:24:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,things are included in,\Nthings are included in.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.92,0:24:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Cooperation, then, means\Nthe respecting of the rights of others
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.92,0:24:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and the moving together.\NSo, a person in this energy level
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.92,0:24:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,who has a used car lot,\Nhe hears that another used car lot
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.92,0:24:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is opening down the block,\Nhe goes into competition with that guy
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.92,0:24:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and feels that he's going to lose.\NSee, he lives in a world of win-lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.92,0:24:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently, he only can see\Nthat he's going to lose
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.92,0:24:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,by the other used car lot opening up\Non the same block.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.92,0:24:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,This person up here in cooperation\Nwhen he hears another used car lot
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.96,0:24:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is opening up on his block\Nsays, fantastic,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.96,0:25:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that'll pull more used car buyers\Nfrom all over the city,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.96,0:25:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,will become, you know,\Nthe center for used cars,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.96,0:25:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and maybe the two of us\Ncan get together and, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.96,0:25:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,advertise together.\NAnd so, he sees working with that guy
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.96,0:25:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that you pull in more\Nso that two used car lots
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.96,0:25:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,will now pull three times\Nas much customers, you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.96,0:25:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of twice as many.\NSo, he wants to join his energies
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.96,0:25:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,with someone else\Nso that everyone benefits
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.96,0:25:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,because he's in to win\Nand win-win.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.96,0:25:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this energy level then\Nis called win-win.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.96,0:25:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I sell more used cars\Nand so do you.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.96,0:25:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The more you advertise,\Nthe better for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.28,0:25:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The more one art gallery advertises,\Nthe better for all the art galleries.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.63,0:25:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what's better for an art gallery\Nthan to have four or five
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.63,0:25:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,in the same building\Nbecause it pulls all the art buyers
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.63,0:25:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,from surrounding communities\Ninto the same building.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.63,0:25:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we move up to the god of,\Nwe move up to the world of,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.75,0:25:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,we move up to the world of love.\NWhat's happened over here, you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.39,0:26:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the process of one is one of revelation\Nand the release of certain endorphins.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.39,0:26:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So, now the person begins to see\Nand experience phenomena
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.84,0:26:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that people down here are not seeing.\NThey're not seeing or experiencing
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.84,0:26:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the lovingness which is also there.\NThis person may see the envy there,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.35,0:26:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,but they don't see\Nthat there is also love there,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.35,0:26:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that although there is envy,\Nthere is also love.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.35,0:26:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The cancellation, the not seeing,\Nthe unable to see,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.64,0:26:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the loveness that goes on\Nbetween all human beings.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.64,0:26:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,This lovingness is going on\Nall the time between everyone
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.18,0:26:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and every circumstance.\NAs this field opens up,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.98,0:26:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,you see that.\NAs you say hello to the doorman,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.98,0:26:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,you realize that there is\Nan enormous lovingness going on there.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.98,0:26:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You're loving the doorman,\Nhe's loving you,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.75,0:26:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and you become a part\Nof his joy of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.75,0:27:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And when I used to live\Nin New York City on Fifth Avenue,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.75,0:27:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a whole routine of doormen\Nthat I said good morning to.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.75,0:27:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you missed one day,\Nthey would say,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.75,0:27:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,where were you yesterday?\NSomething was missing from their life
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.84,0:27:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that was a touch of joy\Nthat that mutual greeting brought,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.84,0:27:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and I miss seeing them.\NI miss seeing their happy face.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.32,0:27:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So, there is a lovingness\Nthat goes on all the time
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.32,0:27:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,in all circumstances,\Nand it's just not visible,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.32,0:27:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,it's just not visible\Nuntil the energy field reaches that point,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.32,0:27:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you begin to see that.\NYou begin to see that
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.39,0:27:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,going on all the time.\NThat it's true, there is this,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.68,0:27:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,but there is also that.\NSee?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.68,0:27:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Down here it's either or,\Nand this begins to include in
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.68,0:27:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,so that you see the lovingness\Nthat is going on all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.68,0:27:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You begin to see the response of nature\Nto your own consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.68,0:28:01.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You begin to become aware\Nthat that which is growing around you,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.41,0:28:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that the energy field\Nthat you are vibrating out
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.41,0:28:07.41,Default,,0,0,0,,is affecting all of life around you,\Nall of life around you.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.41,0:28:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I once killed a plant with consciousness.\NIt was once a plant that I hated,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.15,0:28:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and I didn't like what it stood for.\NI didn't like what I remembered because of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.15,0:28:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't like what it was doing in my life,\Nand I just consciously hated it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.15,0:28:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And in about eight weeks it was dead.\NPoor little plant.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.15,0:28:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like the plant I ever killed, like that.\NAll right, St. Peter, I did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.01,0:28:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I killed it.\NChrist cursed the fig tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.43,0:28:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That's my out.\NThe energy that we radiate out then
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.28,0:28:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,affects all of life around us,\Naffects all of the life around us.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.28,0:28:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And as we move up to this level here,\Nwe begin to see,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.28,0:28:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you cannot read that, of course.\NI can't either.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.28,0:29:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What becomes revealed to you,\Nbecause this is called revelation,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.36,0:29:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,is the incredible beauty of life.\NAs you move towards the top of the box,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.49,0:29:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,it's incredible perfection.\NNot aesthetic beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.97,0:29:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Aesthetic beauty is something else.\NAesthetic beauty is a prettiness, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.23,0:29:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a perception.\NWe're now moving out of the world of perception
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.58,0:29:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,into the world of knowingness,\Nthe inner experience of the incredible essence of all things
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.58,0:29:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,as they express themselves through their perfection.\NThis came to me one day as I was sitting at home
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.64,0:29:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and the kitty was sitting there on the rug.\NAnd I looked at the kitty.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.64,0:29:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Instantly, I got...\NYou know, the kitty is sitting there
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.64,0:29:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,as an absolute perfect expression of its kittiness.\NYou know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.73,0:29:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The kitty sits there and it is itself\Nperfectly, absolutely,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.92,0:30:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in the incredible beauty of its isness being what it is.\NAnd you begin to see that everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.92,0:30:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody has those experiences.\NEverybody in the audience, I'm sure, has had those experiences.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.12,0:30:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll come when you're walking through the woods\Nand suddenly there's that inner silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.56,0:30:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a hushing.\NYou can tell when it's going to happen
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.56,0:30:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,because all of a sudden everything becomes hushed.\NAnd then it slows down
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.60,0:30:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's always to me like a slow motion movie.\NAll of a sudden the incredible,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.60,0:30:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,magnificent,\Nperfection and beauty of all things
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.60,0:30:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and you are one with that\Nand you are not different than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.60,0:30:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That that is what you are.\NAnd you see the truth of all of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.60,0:30:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,God is all that is.\NSo that incredible perfection, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.78,0:30:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And now how do you see people?\NWell, the rose as it is half unfolded,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.88,0:30:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,see, it's unfolding its perfection\Nand absolute perfectness.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.88,0:30:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The incredible beauty, the harmony,\Nits expression of that which it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.83,0:31:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the unfoldingness of that\Nis perfect in its unfoldingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.83,0:31:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And so you look at another human being,\Nyou look at someone,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.83,0:31:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and you see the incredible beauty\Nand it radiates out from their inner self
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.83,0:31:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,almost like a light.\NYou see the incredible beauty
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.83,0:31:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,of the unfoldingness of that which they are\Nas they are coming into the awareness, let's say.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.99,0:31:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Stealing is no longer really good in my life.\NRight, that's the lesson I'm getting.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.99,0:31:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever the lesson is,\Nbooze and drugs are driving me
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.24,0:31:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,into insanity and self-destruction.\NWhatever that lesson is.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.20,0:31:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So those are the perceptual worlds, see?\NThe world being holographic, a hologram.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.91,0:31:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So you all know what a hologram is, right?\NIt's a three-dimensional representation
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.07,0:31:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's done by the interface\Nof a laser light which is aligned photons
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.23,0:32:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and normal light bouncing off an object\Nand creating a photographic plate.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.39,0:32:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you take a fragment of that photographic plate,\Nand you run a laser beam through it again,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.32,0:32:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,it recreates the whole,\Nand it recreates the whole spatially
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.32,0:32:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,in space, three-dimensionally.\NEverything is connected with everything else
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.36,0:32:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,because every person and everything\Nis off a vibration.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.43,0:32:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Obviously, these vibrations all interface, do they not?\NIf you give off a vibration
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.52,0:32:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and you give off a vibration,\Nthen the two must intersect somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.59,0:32:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently, all things are connected\Nwith all other things.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.62,0:32:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is separate from anything else.\NAnd that's the holographic dimension,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.91,0:32:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the title of several very popular books.\NSo this hologram then,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.77,0:32:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the world then, as we see it now,\Nfrom the description of these various,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.77,0:33:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,these are really portholes.\NThese are perceptual portholes
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.87,0:33:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in which we project out\Nthat which we are holding
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.00,0:33:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and then experience back our own projection\Nand say, see, isn't it so?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.86,0:33:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So the world then, the street that we were talking about before,\Nis like a hologram.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.86,0:33:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And starting at the bottom,\Nso as you walk around this hologram,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.76,0:33:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,it goes from all the same hologram.\NAll depends on where you're looking at it from, you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.95,0:33:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the same world.\NBut looked at from here, it's pain and suffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.48,0:33:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, look at the pain and suffering, isn't that terrible?\NAnd the person literally re-experiences
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.48,0:33:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,this pain and suffering.\NThey literally see it on the face.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.48,0:33:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,They hear it in the voice, in the sound,\Nin the vibration.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.48,0:33:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The person in this energy field\Nthen gets back that energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.41,0:33:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and they experience that as what is so.\NJust as the person up here is entranced.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.48,0:34:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, they look at the old people\Nand it almost makes you weep.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.48,0:34:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You look at them and you see the incredible\Nstate of peace and joy that they are into,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.86,0:34:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and inner peace and joy\Nin the divine presence of each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.44,0:34:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the world of perception,\Nthat's the hologram of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.20,0:34:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So how if we see how one experiences\Nthe world that way, then how does one,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.16,0:34:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll extend that to God, huh?\NAnd we'll see something of significance perhaps.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.98,0:34:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So how does God come out then\Nin all of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.91,0:34:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,At the bottom of the box then,\Nout of that apathy,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.91,0:34:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,you see,\Nwe can say that God is dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.20,0:34:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The person who believes in death\Nand absolute destruction,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.83,0:34:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,then God is dead.\NSo one can become a great philosopher.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.18,0:35:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If one has a high IQ,\Nwhat happens is that the mind
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.40,0:35:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,then tends to justify\None's inner position.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.40,0:35:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The intellect comes to the service\Nand tries to make explainable and acceptable
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.40,0:35:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,that the essence of human life is nausea,\Nthat man is hopeless,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.01,0:35:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and that God is dead.\NSo you can become quite popular for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.33,0:35:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Selling books that God is dead.\NGod doesn't really care about all that.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.32,0:35:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So the books go on.\NSo all you're really telling,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.32,0:35:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,what are you telling the world then\Nwhen you write a book about God is dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.32,0:35:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What you're telling the world\Nis your own inner spiritual position
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.32,0:35:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is one of hopelessness and apathy.\NAnd therefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.32,0:35:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to that person,\Nthere is no experience of God,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.32,0:35:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and to them,\NGod is dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.32,0:35:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,To them,\NGod is dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.32,0:35:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind being so powerful,\Nif it holds that God is dead,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.96,0:35:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,then I can assure you\NGod will be dead to that person.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.96,0:36:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,God will be dead to the person\Nwho holds that God is dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.03,0:36:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,There will be no experience of anything\Noutside of one's own personal ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.03,0:36:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So through one's own inner experience,\None can say,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.03,0:36:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never experienced anything\Nother than that which is in the box.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.67,0:36:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of therefore concluding\NI'm a very limited person,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.12,0:36:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and not through conscience,\Ninstead the person projects that
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.12,0:36:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and says God is dead.\NAs we get up higher then,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.98,0:36:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,we get to the conceptualizations\Nof the God of the worm.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.98,0:36:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The sinner you see is a worm,\Nand I being a hopeless sinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.40,0:36:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So these are people who hold that\Nthere may be a God,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.46,0:36:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,but he would not want anything\Nto do with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.46,0:36:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And many of those people indulge\Nin all kinds of self-flagellative activities.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.10,0:36:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You see,\Nthe pursuit of suffering then
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.48,0:36:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,as an assuagement for guilt\Nand the hope that one will reach God,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.48,0:36:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,indulging in an energy field of 30\Nad infinitum
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.92,0:37:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,will not get you to the experience\Nof that which is at 600.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.92,0:37:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore the futility\Nof wallowing in guilt,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.92,0:37:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and penance,\Nand sinfulness,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.92,0:37:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and guiltness,\Nbecause it takes you exactly
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.92,0:37:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to the opposite end of the box.\NGod is not experienced
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.92,0:37:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,in an energy field of 30.\NAs you move up into grief,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.11,0:37:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the God who doesn't want anything\Nto do with you,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.11,0:37:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,those are the people\Nwho are abandoned by God.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.11,0:37:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Abandoned by God.\NI called out to God
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.07,0:37:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and there was no answer.\NAbandoned and separated.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.07,0:37:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Abandoned and separated.\NAs we move up to fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.55,0:37:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,then you move into levels\Nwhere God is the great punisher.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.55,0:37:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,God is what you are terrified of.\NGod who is the avenger.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.19,0:38:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The avenger, the punisher,\Nhe really becomes the persecutor.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.44,0:38:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,He really becomes\Nthat which is demonic.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.38,0:38:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The angry person,\Nthe fearful person,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.38,0:38:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the person who is full\Nof sinfulness then,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.38,0:38:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,can only conceive of a God\Nwho is the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.80,0:38:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the demonic gods.\NIn this way of holding God,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.80,0:38:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,he is capricious,\Nwillful,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.28,0:38:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,he is fitful,\Nand then God took pity
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.28,0:38:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,on the people of something or other\Nand decided not to demolish their city.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.28,0:38:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,This God is also jealous.\NSo he's paranoid.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.44,0:38:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,He's jealous and he's paranoid.\NHe's capricious, he's fitful,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.44,0:38:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and he's the ultimate in destruction.\NHe is not only out to destroy man
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.69,0:38:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and his civilization,\Nhe's out to destroy your soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.69,0:38:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So for one sinful thought,\Nhe will throw you into hell forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.62,0:39:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,This doesn't leave much room for the devil.\NWhat would the devil do
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.48,0:39:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,with this kind of a God around?\NHis job has been taken away totally.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.48,0:39:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What would you fear\Nnext to a God like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.48,0:39:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The worst has already happened.\NDoes it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.48,0:39:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,This is really the God,\Nthe demonic God of hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.87,0:39:17.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It's important because\Nthe next energy level is one of pride
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.87,0:39:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and this demonic conceptualization\Nof God is what often leads
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.12,0:39:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to the next level.\NOn the level of pride,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.32,0:39:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got two positions possible.\NBecause of one's intuitive perception,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.76,0:39:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,inner awareness of truth,\None throws this out.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.76,0:39:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And you may take then on one side\Nthe position of the atheist
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.76,0:39:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,or the agnostic\Nwho comes from the pridefulness
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.30,0:39:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,of the intellect unknowingly.\NHe thinks that's all there is.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.40,0:39:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,He looks at the demonic conceptualizations\Nof God and says,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.40,0:39:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that God isn't even as good as my aunt.\NMy aunt is a more loving being than that
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.40,0:40:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and throws out\Nthe demonic conceptualizations of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.40,0:40:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And then concludes having done so\Nthat he has thrown out God.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.46,0:40:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the error.\NMixing the map with the territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.65,0:40:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,He confuses the map with the territory.\NHaving found an error in the map,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.78,0:40:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,he throws that out thinking\Nhe's now destroyed the territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.78,0:40:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Throwing out the baby with the bathwater.\NHaving thrown out,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.58,0:40:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,what has he thrown out?\NHe's thrown out concepts.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.58,0:40:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But a concept is not the thing.\NA concept is a symbol for the thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.58,0:40:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And in this case,\Na distorted concept.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.64,0:40:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So he throws out the distorted concept\Nand now he has thrown out the thing itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.64,0:40:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That he has handled the matter.\NSo the agnostic says,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.87,0:40:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't take a position about it.\NIt's been handled.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.87,0:40:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all nonsense.\NForget it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.87,0:40:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,No proof one way or the other is possible.\NThinking that the intellect
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.87,0:40:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,is the sum total of human experience.\NThe intellect alone and unaided
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.87,0:40:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot prove the existence of God\Nor disprove it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.87,0:41:04.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And the other side of this field would be\Nthe person who takes the opposite position.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.41,0:41:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That my knowledge of the truth\Nis the only truth there is.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.48,0:41:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore you are wrong.\NAnd you have the endless religious wars
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.48,0:41:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and bigotries.\NThat go on from my position
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.92,0:41:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and my way of seeing it\Nis the only truth and the only way.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.92,0:41:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So the arrogance,\Nthe contempt,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.92,0:41:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,see the denial of the truth\Nthe truth is possible for anybody else.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.92,0:41:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The contempt for their spiritual positions.\NThe defensiveness about one's own spiritual position.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.92,0:41:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore the endless angry\Nconfronts and endless religious wars and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.92,0:41:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That go on on this energy level of pridefulness.\NWhat happens when we get to the level of courage?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.63,0:41:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Because so far we've been below the line.\NWhat happens when you get to the level of courage?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.72,0:41:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You start running into the God of AA.\NSee?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.72,0:42:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,God of AA.\NYou start running into the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.72,0:42:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,For the first time now you're above the line.\NAnd what is the truth?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.72,0:42:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth is you don't know anything about God, do you?\NThe truth is you have a lot of hearsay.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.46,0:42:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Written by very authoritative and impressive people.\NComing from authoritative sources.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.46,0:42:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And what is your own inner knowledge and experience of the truth of that?\NIt's zilch.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.46,0:42:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And so,\Nin AA they talk about the God of your own understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.46,0:42:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The God of your own inner experience.\NThe truth that has come to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.46,0:42:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Not the truth that has come to some saint 2,000 years ago\Non the other side of the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.46,0:42:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,walking on the road to something.\NWhen you're walking down the street and your knees go to water
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.20,0:42:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and you need a drink or you need a fix\Nwhat happened to somebody else a couple thousand years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.20,0:42:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,is not going to come to your aid.\NWhat you've realized, the experience of that which is present within you now
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.20,0:43:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,is what you need right this second.\NWhen the desire to drink or take a drug hits you
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.45,0:43:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got to have something that is right here, right now\Nand rock-like connected within you.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.45,0:43:10.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That services you.\NThat's experienced within you.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.45,0:43:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That's real.\NThat is.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.93,0:43:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That is for you what is real.\NAnd so you have the God of eminence
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.93,0:43:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, in theological terms.\NThe God of transcendence is out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.96,0:43:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The God of transcendence is not of much use.\NThe God of transcendence is what everybody tried in religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.96,0:43:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And people in AA, including the priesthood that's there\Nwill say the God of religion I tried.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.96,0:43:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I tried that.\NThe God who is out there was of no use.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.96,0:43:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to come into AA\Nto find the inner experience of the reality of the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.96,0:43:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The God that is within me.\NThe God that in theological terms
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.96,0:43:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,is the God that was imminent.\NThat which is within myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.38,0:43:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the God of AA.\NGod as you understand him.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.38,0:44:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's understood in AA\Nthat as you grow, as you transcend in the box
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.38,0:44:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,your experience of God will then\Nparallel that inner growth
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.38,0:44:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and your experiences will be commensurate with that.\NYou then move up, as we say, to a God of mercy.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.80,0:44:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the God of unforgivingness.\NThis is the God of forgiveness.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.80,0:44:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the God of love\Nand mercy.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.68,0:44:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,AA says\Nit acknowledges only one authority
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.84,0:44:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is a loving God.\NAnd they mean by that a loving God expressed
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.83,0:44:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,through your own individual experience\Nand through the group consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.83,0:44:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Through the conscience of the group.\NAnd so people learn to rely on sponsorship
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.83,0:44:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,because they ask\Nthat through that
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.05,0:44:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the will of God be known in their own personal life.\NAnd they begin to experience
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.05,0:45:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that that energy field which is coming through the group\Nis that expression of God
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.47,0:45:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,as it comes into their life\Nin the group experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.04,0:45:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The God of love, the God of mercy.\NWe start moving up into the God of oneness.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.04,0:45:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The God of oneness.\NWe start moving into that God of perfection.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.04,0:45:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally as we get near the box\Nthe top of the box
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.04,0:45:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,we move into the experience of the presence itself.\NThe experience of the presence itself
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.20,0:45:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,which is often called illumination.\NThose states described by the saints
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.20,0:45:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,usually associated with sainthood.\NThe total overwhelming experience
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.10,0:45:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,of the divine presence.\NIneffable.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.56,0:45:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Overwhelming.\NTransforming.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.56,0:45:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Even a few moments of that experience\Ntransforms one's life.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.76,0:45:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the experience of Bill Wilson of course\Nwhen Bill surrendered.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.04,0:46:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,In that moment he asked\Nis there a God?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.04,0:46:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And if there is, I asked him\NI asked to experience him.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.11,0:46:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And in one instant the room lit up.\NAnd he felt the infinite presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.11,0:46:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And out of that moment\Nout of that second
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.46,0:46:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,all of AA was born.\NAll of the transformation that has occurred
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.46,0:46:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,in social consciousness.\NThe whole self-help group movement
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.46,0:46:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,in all of America\Nof which AA was the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.91,0:46:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,They now run into the hundreds.\NThere is no human ailment or dilemma.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.91,0:46:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,That there now is not some place\Nthat you can go
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.91,0:46:34.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and experience human understanding\Nand help from that absolute authority
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.91,0:46:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,that comes from only having lived that yourself.\NThe power of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.91,0:46:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,See, having lived it yourself\Ngives you the power of healing that
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.91,0:46:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,which you have healed within yourself.\NThat whole awareness of that
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.07,0:46:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,came out of that one second.\NWhat a powerful moment that was.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.07,0:46:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That moment transformed\Nall of therapy in the United States.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.10,0:47:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Transformed the whole mental health movement.\NTook us out of hopelessness.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.26,0:47:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,In this case, in the beginning\Nit was just alcohol.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.55,0:47:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The condition of alcoholism\Nwas a hopeless condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.41,0:47:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Hopeless.\NThere was no cure for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.41,0:47:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no help for it.\NInterestingly, out of Carl Jung
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.60,0:47:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,it was Carl Jung's integrity\Nand honesty
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.34,0:47:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that accounted for the birth of AA.\NBecause when Roland saw Carl Jung
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.34,0:47:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and thought he was cured\Nand then he went back to the United States
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.44,0:47:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and he fell back into this state.\NHe went back to Carl Jung
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.01,0:47:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and Carl said,\NAlas, but my science, my art cannot help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.20,0:47:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But there have been times\Nin the history of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.20,0:47:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,where people with this affliction\Nhave thrown themselves into a spiritual group.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.20,0:47:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And there have been reported throughout man's history\Nisolated cases
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.24,0:47:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,in which out of this experience\Na recovery has been possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.24,0:47:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But I myself offer you no hope.\NAnd so Roland went back to the United States
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.24,0:48:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,in a state of hopelessness.\NTotal hopelessness.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.24,0:48:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,But he followed Carl's advice\Nand he went to the Oxford Groups.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.49,0:48:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The Oxford Groups being based on\Nbasically the 12 steps.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.49,0:48:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,A shortened version of the 12 steps.\NIt was out of that hopelessness then
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.97,0:48:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,that Roland surrendered.\NAnd out of his surrender
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.97,0:48:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,he achieved sobriety\Nand then passed it on through Bill.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.97,0:48:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Nyou see the great power then
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.61,0:48:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,of surrender.\NThe space that allows for grace.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.61,0:48:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The great power of grace.\NIn just the moment that Bill
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.06,0:48:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,experienced that experience\Nall of what came forth
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.06,0:48:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,it's as though he\Nin opening himself to that power
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.06,0:48:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,of God within him\Nit's like he opened a window for the God energy
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.06,0:48:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,to flow into the planet.\NAnd from that experience then
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.06,0:48:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,all of AA and all of it was born.\NThe enormous transforming power
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.06,0:49:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,of such moments.\NAnd as a child I experienced some of these states.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.35,0:49:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And in teenage\NI had a paper route one time.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.35,0:49:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It was in northern Wisconsin.\NIt was 20 below zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.96,0:49:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,A terrible blizzard.\NAnd to get out of the cold wind
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.96,0:49:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I made a hole in a snow bank.\NAnd as I sat in the snow bank
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.02,0:49:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to get out of the blizzard\Nan incredible state came on.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.92,0:49:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Of infinite peace.\NIncredible. Indescribable.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.92,0:49:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,No one was touched by\NGod himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.84,0:49:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And all that I was was\Nreplaced with light.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.13,0:49:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And this incredible infinite state.\NAnd that which was personal
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.13,0:49:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,David no longer was\Nexperienced.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.16,0:49:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And so those states\Ncome into everyone's life
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.19,0:49:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,briefly or\Nin this case unsought.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.25,0:49:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But there was no context in which to hold it.\NThere was no context
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.38,0:50:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,in which this 14 year old\Ncould hold that experience
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.38,0:50:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,meaningfully.\NAnd when it returned in
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.53,0:50:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,January 1965\Nagain
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.79,0:50:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,there was no pre-existing\Ncontext in which to hold
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.79,0:50:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the experience of the presence\Nof the infinite omniscience
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.36,0:50:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and omnipresence.\NAnd that lasted for about a year
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.75,0:50:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,in that period.\NAnd then in January 1981
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.91,0:50:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,again that state came on\Nrunning up in the numbers in the
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.97,0:50:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,United States.\NAnd so having personally gone up and down
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.45,0:50:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole scale\Nof those experiences
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.45,0:50:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and then\Ncoming out of that with
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.77,0:50:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the desire to create\Nthe context
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.89,0:50:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to create a way in which to hold all that\Nso that all can be purified
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.89,0:50:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,within the way that you're holding it\Nso that it becomes a permanent
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.89,0:51:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,experience.\NSo that those people who've had those experiences
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.56,0:51:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,come out of it with that\Nrealization.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.60,0:51:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,With kinesiology we'll\Njust test the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.63,0:51:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,of some of these experiences especially\Nthe essential
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.82,0:51:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,point that I'm trying to make\Nand that is what one is addicted to.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.82,0:51:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you realize\Nwhat you are addicted to
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.85,0:51:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,what it is that you seek\Nby addicted to I mean that desire
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.98,0:51:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,to return to that experience\Nthe overwhelming desire to return
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.98,0:51:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,to that experience.\NOnce you've experienced the presence
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.98,0:51:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,there is nothing that this world has to offer\Nat all.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.98,0:51:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It dissolves into a space\Nthrough it that you move through
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.98,0:51:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,to return to that experience.\NAll of life then becomes transformed.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.98,0:51:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all held within a different context.\NAnd so
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.40,0:51:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought we'd do some kinesiology.\NHow many here have never experienced kinesiology?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.40,0:52:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe a third of the class.\NAlright. Kinesiology is very
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.61,0:52:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,simple in that what you're testing\Nis energy and energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.61,0:52:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,as it expresses itself in\Nparticular power.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.77,0:52:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,How about if I get a subject\Na willing subject from the audience.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.77,0:52:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I may want to be the subject.\NWho's seen kinesiology before?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.77,0:52:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like to come up and just be the\Nperson that I demonstrated with?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.52,0:52:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What kinesiology is testing\Nis the integrity of an energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.56,0:52:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,as it expresses itself\Nin the harmony and balance of
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.56,0:52:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the acupuncture system.\NThe acupuncture system
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.56,0:52:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,running down twelve meridians is everybody\Nin California
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.56,0:52:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,generally sophisticated about such matters.\NRunning down the
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.75,0:52:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,twelve meridians, right?\NThe minute you
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.48,0:52:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,see the minute you go above the line\Nwhen you go above the line you instantly
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.68,0:53:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,go strong. When you go below\Nthe line you instantly go weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.68,0:53:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's a very neat way to test\Nthe truth of anything by
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.68,0:53:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,asking for the integrity of the energy\Nfield. What you're testing is the integrity
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.68,0:53:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,of an energy field. But\Nwhat we'll do today is demonstrate the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.68,0:53:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,of some of the things we've been saying with kinesiology.\NSo what we do is we ask
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.68,0:53:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the subject and we're going to do this as a class.\NWe'll become ones and twos.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.68,0:53:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,One becomes the tester, one the testee.\NIt's important to experience the truth of this
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.68,0:53:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,because otherwise you'll just hold it in intellect.\NOnce you experience the truth of what we're saying
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.68,0:53:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,it really changes your life.\NSo what you do is you raise
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.80,0:53:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,your left arm, the person is being tested\Nand you have them look at the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.80,0:53:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Look straight ahead at the wall\Nand don't smile at the person because
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.80,0:53:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,if you smile at them you're radiating out an energy\Nfield up in here and you're affecting
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.80,0:53:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the response. So you try to be\Ndetached, clinically detached
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.80,0:53:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and have them look at the wall\Nand then when I press down you resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.80,0:53:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, thank you.\NNow, you can let her down.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.99,0:54:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,When you test, you test with two fingers\Nand what you're testing is for a general feeling
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.99,0:54:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,of the person's muscular strength.\NYou're not trying to break their arm and see.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.99,0:54:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You know. You're just trying to\Nget a feeling for their power, for their energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.99,0:54:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You press down with two fingers.\NTwo fingers.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.20,0:54:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,When you do that, I'm going to ask him to hold\Nsomething in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.97,0:54:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, I want you to hold in mind somebody you don't\Nlike or somebody you've experienced
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.97,0:54:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,unpleasantly or something in your life\Nthat's not so great.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.24,0:54:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that is something that is below the line.\NSomebody he fears, somebody he hates,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.24,0:54:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,an experience that is unpleasant,\Na regret, a grief.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.24,0:54:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, now I'd like you to hold in mind\Nsomeone you love.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.29,0:54:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It could be your kitty, it could be your dog,\Nit could be Jesus, it could be your mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.29,0:54:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it? Thank you.\NSee?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.09,0:55:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is above the line, the truth,\Nlove being that
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.09,0:55:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,not different than that which is the truth,\Nempowers.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.09,0:55:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is a lie weakens.\NAnd the integrity of the energy
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.09,0:55:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,fuel can be tested out instantly.\NIt has widespread
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.32,0:55:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,applications once it begins to dawn on\Nyou that you can get the truth of
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.32,0:55:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,things that are beyond your personal opinion.\NBefore you read
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.38,0:55:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,a book, before you wander in the metaphysical\Nshop and decide that
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.38,0:55:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Swami so-and-so is going to be your savior,\Nit's very neat to test out
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.38,0:55:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,what his integrity field is and what his intention\Nis and the space that he's coming
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.44,0:55:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,from. So you'll find\Nthat it has very important
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.89,0:55:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,clinical applications and we'll\Nexperience some of them today.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.89,0:55:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's divide up into ones and\Ntwos and we're going to test out three or four
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.08,0:55:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,propositions and\Nthen at the end you can ask a secret
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.08,0:55:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,question and get an answer to that which you've\Nalways wanted to know the truth of.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.08,0:56:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And get a\Nreasonable assurance that you're
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.92,0:56:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,getting the truth. So why don't we just\Ndivide up into ones and twos
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.92,0:56:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and all of us stand up.\NNumber one is going to be the tester,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.04,0:56:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,number two is going to be the testee,\Nthen we'll switch. Number two will
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.04,0:56:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,become the testor, number one\Nthe testee.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.55,0:56:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So here's what I'd like you to do is\Nto not say anything. This can all be done
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.55,0:56:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,in silence. If you just listen to me it'll go\Nvery fast and it'll be quite a rewarding
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.55,0:56:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,experience. Just decide who's number\None. Number one put up your hand so we
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.55,0:56:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,know who's your number one. Okay, you are the doctor.\NAnd number two is the testee.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.55,0:56:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So the first thing I'd like you to do\Nis just to ask them to hold out their
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.55,0:56:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,arm and test\Ntheir arm just like I did with him
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.55,0:56:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,with two fingers. And don't forget\Nyou're not trying to break his arm, their arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.09,0:56:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You're just trying to get a feel for their power\Nand their strength. Try to be detached
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.28,0:56:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and impersonal as though it was\Na clinical research.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.28,0:56:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So you look\Nat the wall and just
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.28,0:57:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,ask them to resist.\NWhen they're ready, have them resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.57,0:57:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So you get a feeling for their power and their energy.\NOkay? Got it? Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.21,0:57:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Now everybody then, the first thing I'd like\Nyou to do, those who are being tested, is hold
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.21,0:57:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,in mind or picture or\Nremember something or someone
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.21,0:57:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that's unpleasant in some regard.\NSome loss that you've experienced,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.21,0:57:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,an accident, something coming up in the\Nfuture that you wish you didn't have to face,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.21,0:57:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,a ticket you got for\Nsomething. If all fails
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.36,0:57:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,picture yourself tied to a railroad track in the\Ntrain is bearing down and getting closer.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.36,0:57:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone you don't like\Nfrom the past. Someone you don't like
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.62,0:57:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,in your present life. Somebody you fear.\NSomebody who scares you, really.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.77,0:57:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody who really scares you when you\Ncome up against it.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.22,0:57:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Has everybody got that?\NNow I'd like you to hold something
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.35,0:58:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,or someone that you love.\NAs I said, it could be your kitty, it could be your
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.86,0:58:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,dog, it could be your mom, lover, girlfriend,\Nmom, dad. You can change
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.36,0:58:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,arms if you want. First get acquainted with the\Npower of that arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.36,0:58:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,As I say, don't push so hard you wear them out.\NWith two fingers
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.40,0:58:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you can get a feeling. They're either weak or they're strong.\NThat's all you need to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.40,0:58:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,There's got to be somebody you love.\NSome value that you cherish.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.91,0:58:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Some space that is very\Nsacred to you. Anything that
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.94,0:58:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,is loving.\NThat's an amazing
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.08,0:58:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,experience, is it not?\NThe next thing I want to test out is a proposition.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.20,0:58:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So get ready to be tested.\NI'm going to give you the proposition. I want you to hold this
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.20,0:58:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,proposition in mind.\NAnd then when you have got the proposition in mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.96,0:58:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,nod your head so that the person can\Npress down and test you.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.96,0:59:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The proposition is that the drugs have the power\Nto get you high.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.38,0:59:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The power is in the drugs.\NIt's drugs that get me high.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.64,0:59:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's drugs that have the power to create\Nthat experience within
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.19,0:59:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,either myself or those who are addicted.\NMakes no difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.36,0:59:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just an alternate proposition\Nso you can get ready to be tested
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.36,0:59:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and hold this concept in mind.\NThe truth is that the drugs remove the obstruction
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.70,0:59:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,to the experience of that which I am\Nand allow me to experience the bliss
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.70,0:59:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,of that which is my own higher self.\NThe drugs block the not-self
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.34,0:59:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and allow me to get closer to\Nthe experience of my own inner self.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.60,0:59:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The power comes from my own inner\Ngodness.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.17,1:00:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That is the source of the power\Nof that experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.30,1:00:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the next thing is you're going to ask\Na question.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.07,1:00:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything you always really want to know\Nthe answer to.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.32,1:00:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,If you have an addictive problem\Nand you have a question in your mind
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.32,1:00:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,you can say,\NAm I really addicted?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.32,1:00:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I really an alcoholic?\NDo I really have a problem with that?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.60,1:00:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You can ask any question you want\Nand then just indicate to the tester
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.69,1:00:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,as long as it's answerable by yes or no.\NSo you don't have to share this question
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.24,1:00:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,you can just keep it in mind.\NIf there's anything you really want to know,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.16,1:00:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,ask either that.\NIs the boss planning to fire me?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.58,1:00:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Should I really see a doctor about that?\NWhatchamacallit.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.08,1:01:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever you really want to know, ask about.\NDoes my mother really love me?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.63,1:01:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you know.\NIs my kitty really pregnant?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:17.41,1:01:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, any kind of question you want.\NAm I really pregnant?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.89,1:01:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, now we'll switch.\NWe'll switch and again
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.82,1:01:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,if you're silent I'll just guide you\Nthrough it and we'll do it quickly.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.40,1:01:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,First test the strength of the person\Nso you get a feel for it.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.40,1:01:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Just use two fingers.\NHave the person resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.22,1:01:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist with all your strength.\NOkay, got that.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.99,1:01:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The next thing you hold in mind\Nis someone you don't like.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.99,1:01:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Something you don't like.\NSomething painful.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.18,1:02:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Painful memory from the past.\NSomething you wish hadn't happened.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.69,1:02:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Something you fear might happen.\NSomebody who blows your mind
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.59,1:02:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,when you see them.\NThe devil.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.12,1:02:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold the devil back there.\NAlright, now in contrast
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.36,1:02:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,just hold in mind the presence\Nthe memory of someone you love.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.71,1:02:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Their image, their thought.\NA memory of being with them.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.03,1:02:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Sound of their voice.\NWhat they feel like to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.63,1:02:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What they look like to you.\NHold it and test that.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.86,1:02:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really dramatic, isn't it?\NI mean it is so definite.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.86,1:02:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It is so strong.\NIt is so powerful.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.68,1:02:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It is so overwhelming.\NOkay, the next thing because we're
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.68,1:02:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,into the consciousness about addictions.\NWe want to hold in mind, get ready to be tested
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.68,1:03:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and then hold this concept in mind.\NIt's the drugs that have the power
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.77,1:03:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to get me high.\NThe experience of bliss comes from the drug.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.22,1:03:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Drugs have the power to create that experience.\NTest the truth of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.31,1:03:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, now hold the contrasting proposition in mind\Nto be tested on this one.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.31,1:03:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That the drugs block off\Nthe experience
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.34,1:03:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,of my lower self and allow me\Nto experience the energy field
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.34,1:03:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,or get close to the energy field\Nof that which is my higher self.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.52,1:03:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The experience in consciousness that comes about\Nfrom the use of drugs
Dialogue: 0,1:03:44.93,1:03:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,from intoxication\Nis literally the experience
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.93,1:04:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,of my own inner presence.\NAnd now everybody gets a secret question.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.79,1:04:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Or questions.\NSecret question.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.43,1:04:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you really want to know?\NLet's face the truth of the answer.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.60,1:04:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The answer you get now, of course,\Nis the way it is now.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.60,1:04:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not set in cement.\NSo if you get an answer that you don't like,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.89,1:04:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,realize it's not set in cement.\NThat you have the power to transform
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.21,1:04:48.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that entire relationship\Nor situation
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.21,1:04:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and transform it within your life\Nso that you can get a retest sometime later
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.21,1:04:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,holding it from a different space\Nand get a different answer.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.21,1:05:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,But that is the way you're holding it now\Nand the way it's going to come out.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.66,1:05:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The way you're holding it now.\NSo that's sort of a fun experience, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.11,1:05:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,A way of\Nascertaining the integrity
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.13,1:05:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,of an energy field.\NWhat you're testing is the energy field.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.23,1:05:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you hold something or someone in mind\Nyou're asking what is the
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.23,1:05:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,integrity of this person's intention\Nor energy field in my life.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.26,1:05:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Generally, the experience\Nthat I get when I work with families
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.26,1:05:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,is the same as we do with the addicts.\NWith the people who have become addicted
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.26,1:05:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,we've been doing it for a couple of years\Nat the villa and the answers have always
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.26,1:05:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,been the same.\NWhen we ask, does the drug have the power
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.25,1:05:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,to create the experience\Nwithin yourself, they all go weak.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.25,1:05:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And when we say\Nis the truth that the drug
Dialogue: 0,1:05:52.34,1:05:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,blocks that which you are not\Nso you can experience
Dialogue: 0,1:05:56.34,1:06:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,or at least get into the ballpark\Nof the experience of the truth of your
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.34,1:06:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,inner godness, they all go strong.\NSo at least within the addict population
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.34,1:06:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the one I've had the experience with\Nit's been verifiable right across the board.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.34,1:06:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It is obvious\Nas you listen to
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.17,1:06:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,what we're saying today\Nthat no chemical has the power
Dialogue: 0,1:06:17.17,1:06:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to create a 600 experience.\NWhat are the energy fields
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.30,1:06:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,of some of the things in our daily life\Nand our daily experience
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.30,1:06:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and what can we learn from that\Nand how can we use that
Dialogue: 0,1:06:29.30,1:06:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,in a way that's beneficial.\NHow can we end up holding
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.33,1:06:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,this information in such a way that\Nhealing comes out of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.33,1:06:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That being the purpose of the communication.\NWe notice that
Dialogue: 0,1:06:42.00,1:06:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the science and medicine\Nthat which pertains
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.00,1:06:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,to the mind, to the intellect\Nto the mind with a small m
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.16,1:06:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,that which pertains to the intellect\Nand calibrates in an energy field
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.20,1:06:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,of about 425.\NSee that's the difficulty of the atheist
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.20,1:07:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,or the agnostic.\NComing from an energy field of the intellect
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.20,1:07:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,which is 425\Nhow can you have any experience
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.23,1:07:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,of that which is outside the domain\Nof the intellect and calibrates
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.23,1:07:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,at 600 and up.\NThat which is 425 cannot experience
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.26,1:07:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is 600 and up.\NAt 450
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.68,1:07:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,we run into that\Nwhich we call harmony.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:22.68,1:07:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is cooperative.\NSo competition is 180.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:26.74,1:07:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We say competition\Nis 180
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.74,1:07:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and cooperation\Nis about 450.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.09,1:07:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually cooperation runs about 480.\NHarmony,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.12,1:07:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,comparison as they move through\Neducation
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.46,1:07:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,you might say\Nmoves up through into that which is harmonious
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.46,1:07:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and that which is cooperative\Nand at 475
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.65,1:07:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,we see is the calibration\Nof hope.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:57.65,1:08:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,In AA they talk about\Nwe share our experience, our strength
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.65,1:08:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and our hope.\NWhat are the energy fields that are being
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.75,1:08:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,shared?\NOur experience of having gone through this whole experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.75,1:08:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The hope.\NThe inspiration that comes out of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.88,1:08:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Our experience, our strength\Nand our hope.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:18.13,1:08:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And strength being over here.\NAs you move up into
Dialogue: 0,1:08:23.03,1:08:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,these heart levels then\Nat about 530
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.03,1:08:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,we have simplicity.\NIn which the complexities of life
Dialogue: 0,1:08:31.03,1:08:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,are now experienced because of one's\Ninner values
Dialogue: 0,1:08:35.03,1:08:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and they're held in a different way.\NThey're held in a different way.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.03,1:08:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And at 540 you have gratitude.\NSo you know 12 step groups
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.12,1:08:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,talk a great deal about gratitude.\NGratitude to the program.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.12,1:08:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Gratitude to Bill.\NGratitude
Dialogue: 0,1:08:52.02,1:08:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,gratitude for their sobriety.\NGratitude to the grace of God.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:56.21,1:09:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore the gratitude itself\Nbecause this is the same
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.21,1:09:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,energy level as healing.\NHealing and AA and gratitude
Dialogue: 0,1:09:04.40,1:09:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,all come out about the same.\NThat which is grateful
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.40,1:09:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is healing\Nand AA all come out about
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.44,1:09:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the same. So gratitude then\Nis really a way of self healing.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.50,1:09:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,To be able to hold a thing\Nfrom gratitude.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.56,1:09:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you begin to see then how\Nsome of the things in the lower part of the box
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.56,1:09:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,can be healed.\NThey can be healed
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.56,1:09:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,from the way in which they are held.\NFrom the way in which
Dialogue: 0,1:09:33.72,1:09:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,they are held.\NSo we said that worldly success
Dialogue: 0,1:09:37.72,1:09:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,was about 200.\NThat doesn't mean you should throw out
Dialogue: 0,1:09:41.72,1:09:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,worldly success at all.\NWhat it means is
Dialogue: 0,1:09:45.72,1:09:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,one can be grateful for that worldly success.\NIf one can say
Dialogue: 0,1:09:49.84,1:09:54.45,Default,,0,0,0,,thank you God\Nfor this enormous abundance.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:54.45,1:09:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,For the enormous opening I have\Nto utilize
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.80,1:10:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that which I have power over\Nto communicate that which is helpful to the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:03.80,1:10:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So\Nto hold from love then
Dialogue: 0,1:10:08.18,1:10:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,one's sexual opportunities\None's power in the world
Dialogue: 0,1:10:12.18,1:10:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,one's status. All these things.\NNow the way you hold them
Dialogue: 0,1:10:16.18,1:10:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,begins to transform them.\NThe way you hold your own past.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:20.18,1:10:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,If you say thank you\Nas painful as it was
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.28,1:10:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I could not have learned that lesson\Nwithout having experienced it out.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:28.60,1:10:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It was possible for me to learn that\Nsome other way I would have.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.60,1:10:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Obviously because I experienced it out\Nfor me it was necessary
Dialogue: 0,1:10:36.60,1:10:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,to move from this space to that space\Nto have lived it out
Dialogue: 0,1:10:40.60,1:10:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and experienced it through.\NSo it opens then
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.30,1:10:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,an awareness of how we can begin\Nto hold things
Dialogue: 0,1:10:49.30,1:10:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,so that they become healing\Nso that they become sacred
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.30,1:10:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,because of our touch\Nbecause of the touch of how we are holding them.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:58.10,1:11:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And at 570 then\Nyou become aware
Dialogue: 0,1:11:02.10,1:11:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,of that inner beauty\Nthe incredible beauty
Dialogue: 0,1:11:06.10,1:11:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,in all of creation.\NAnd that beauty
Dialogue: 0,1:11:10.13,1:11:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and its perfection\Nthe incredible beauty
Dialogue: 0,1:11:16.47,1:11:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,we see that the source of it\Nis that which is sacred.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:20.47,1:11:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The sacredness of all of creation\Nis the sacredness of life itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:24.47,1:11:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The incredible beauty\Nof its expression
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.47,1:11:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and its absolute perfection\Nas one gets near the top of the box.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:33.01,1:11:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And out of that\Nout of that experience
Dialogue: 0,1:11:37.01,1:11:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,then comes compassion.\NThe importance of these three things
Dialogue: 0,1:11:42.71,1:11:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,of courage\Nof love
Dialogue: 0,1:11:46.71,1:11:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and of compassion\Nbecause those are points of decision
Dialogue: 0,1:11:50.71,1:11:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,which you can access\Nthe higher states of consciousness yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:54.71,1:11:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,To face the truth about things\Neven though it may be painful.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:59.51,1:12:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Your commitment to lovingness\Nas the way you wish to be
Dialogue: 0,1:12:03.51,1:12:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,as the experience\Nof how you want to experience your life
Dialogue: 0,1:12:07.51,1:12:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and how you value it\Nthe lovingness for your own life
Dialogue: 0,1:12:11.89,1:12:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and that of others\Nand the development of compassion
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.89,1:12:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the revelation\Nbecause of the release
Dialogue: 0,1:12:20.15,1:12:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,then on the physical plane\Nthe endorphins
Dialogue: 0,1:12:24.76,1:12:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the opening into the understanding of the human heart\Nto clear up something else
Dialogue: 0,1:12:29.20,1:12:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,that came up during the break\Nthat release of the endorphins
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.27,1:12:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,is coming from one's spiritual position.\NIt's important to realize
Dialogue: 0,1:12:37.27,1:12:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,that the body\Nand all that goes on with it
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.27,1:12:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,is coming out of life.\NIt is life that creates the body.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:45.27,1:12:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It is one's spiritual position\Nit is that commitment
Dialogue: 0,1:12:49.27,1:12:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and the exercise of that lovingness\Nwhich releases the endorphins
Dialogue: 0,1:12:53.27,1:12:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,it is not the other way around.\NYou can't, in other words
Dialogue: 0,1:12:57.59,1:13:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,take endorphins and find yourself\Nin a high spiritual state.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:02.48,1:13:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a confusion of causality.\NThis world being the world
Dialogue: 0,1:13:06.48,1:13:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,a manifest world of the expression\Nof that which you are holding.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:10.48,1:13:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It really is not linear\Nit is not as though there are two different levels
Dialogue: 0,1:13:14.80,1:13:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,it is not as though\Nwhat is being held in mind is now
Dialogue: 0,1:13:18.80,1:13:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,cause and what is being expressed\Nin the world is effect.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:22.80,1:13:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Although in a certain way\Nof holding it that would be so.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:27.44,1:13:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually they both go on\Nsimultaneously cause being
Dialogue: 0,1:13:31.44,1:13:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,outside of the field of both.\NCause is outside the field of both.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:36.05,1:13:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is cause\Ncreates both its representation
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.15,1:13:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,in the manifest world\Nand the way it is held in mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:44.15,1:13:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that interesting?\NI get going on causality
Dialogue: 0,1:13:51.68,1:13:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that's a whole other trip.\NBut that compassion then
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.51,1:14:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,is that desire\Nthat ability
Dialogue: 0,1:14:01.83,1:14:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,that dedication\Nto understanding.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:05.83,1:14:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,To understand the heart\Nand as you see it's
Dialogue: 0,1:14:09.83,1:14:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,way beyond condemnation\Nit is beyond right and wrong
Dialogue: 0,1:14:13.89,1:14:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,it is an understanding\Nof the nature and the essence
Dialogue: 0,1:14:17.89,1:14:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,of life itself.\NAnd just at that level then
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.53,1:14:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,at 600\Ncomes about things that we call wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:26.63,1:14:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And\Nintrinsic to a person at that level
Dialogue: 0,1:14:30.63,1:14:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is an inner gentleness.\NAnd with gentleness
Dialogue: 0,1:14:34.72,1:14:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,goes strength.\NThat which is the most powerful
Dialogue: 0,1:14:38.95,1:14:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,in the universe\Nis the most gentle.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:43.14,1:14:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And as that experience comes into you\Nthe thing that totally
Dialogue: 0,1:14:47.14,1:14:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,wipes you out\Nis its profound gentleness.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:51.14,1:14:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It is so exquisite\Nas that awareness
Dialogue: 0,1:14:55.14,1:15:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,dawns on you\Nthat it's almost
Dialogue: 0,1:15:00.13,1:15:04.29,Default,,0,0,0,,insufferable to experience it.\NThat is the response
Dialogue: 0,1:15:04.29,1:15:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,of the remaining ego.\NAs the presence
Dialogue: 0,1:15:08.80,1:15:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,as you become aware of the presence\Nit disappears
Dialogue: 0,1:15:12.96,1:15:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,as the presence becomes all it is.\NBut in the beginning
Dialogue: 0,1:15:16.96,1:15:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,there is that feeling of awe\Nand the incredible nature
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.05,1:15:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,of that exquisite gentleness.\NAlso
Dialogue: 0,1:15:26.88,1:15:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,its incredible power.\NIt is not only exquisitely
Dialogue: 0,1:15:30.88,1:15:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,gentle beyond description\Nbut its power
Dialogue: 0,1:15:34.88,1:15:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,is indescribable.\NIts power is
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.78,1:15:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,absolute and therefore\Nthe experience is curiously
Dialogue: 0,1:15:43.78,1:15:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,one of this\Nexquisite gentleness
Dialogue: 0,1:15:49.09,1:15:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the presence of infinite power\Nand at the same time
Dialogue: 0,1:15:53.16,1:15:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,it is rock-like.\NI've never read that in any place but
Dialogue: 0,1:15:58.56,1:16:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a rock-like\Nnature to the quality
Dialogue: 0,1:16:02.56,1:16:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,of that which is exquisitely\Ngentle and also
Dialogue: 0,1:16:06.56,1:16:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,all-powerful and\Nperfect.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:10.92,1:16:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And in that level\Ncomes that which we have
Dialogue: 0,1:16:15.14,1:16:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,at the top of the board\Nthat which is beyond all
Dialogue: 0,1:16:19.17,1:16:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the peace of God.\NAnd as that state approaches
Dialogue: 0,1:16:24.74,1:16:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the intrinsic innocence\Nwith all things
Dialogue: 0,1:16:29.00,1:16:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,which is part and results\Nin compassion.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:33.19,1:16:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Exquisite awareness that within\Nthat the essence of all things
Dialogue: 0,1:16:37.28,1:16:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,in its perfection\Nis that absolute innocence.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:41.28,1:16:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you see\Nthat innocence?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:46.63,1:16:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's as though the mind\Nis like a computer.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:53.19,1:16:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's as though the mind\Nof the child.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:58.05,1:17:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens to the mind\Nof the child? The mind of the child
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.05,1:17:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,is in a state of innocence.\NAnd then what happens
Dialogue: 0,1:17:06.18,1:17:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind of the child\Nis like the hardware you might say
Dialogue: 0,1:17:10.18,1:17:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,is that the programs of the world\Ncome in like the software
Dialogue: 0,1:17:14.18,1:17:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and begin to program it.\NAnd what makes the child programmable?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:18.63,1:17:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,What makes the child\Nprogrammable?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:22.85,1:17:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it not its intrinsic innocence?\NIt's because you love your mother
Dialogue: 0,1:17:27.62,1:17:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that whatever she says\Nyou incorporate as your own.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:33.28,1:17:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you love your dad\Nbecause you love your country
Dialogue: 0,1:17:37.28,1:17:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you love your teacher\Nbecause you hold them in respect and honor them
Dialogue: 0,1:17:41.28,1:17:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that's why you believe what they say.\NIt's because of the love of your peers
Dialogue: 0,1:17:45.28,1:17:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and wanting to be one of them.\NOut of your love for them.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:49.89,1:17:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So that intrinsic innocence\Nwhich is there
Dialogue: 0,1:17:55.04,1:17:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,never changes.\NThe hardware of the computer
Dialogue: 0,1:17:59.52,1:18:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,never changes no matter what software\Nfloppy disk you put in, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.52,1:18:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is the computer itself\Nnever loses its innocence.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.52,1:18:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You just can hear different programs\Nput in a different program.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:12.61,1:18:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And so\Nthe awareness of the presence
Dialogue: 0,1:18:17.76,1:18:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,of that within\Nbecause it never leaves you.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:22.92,1:18:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's what's listening to my voice\Nright now, is it not?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:28.26,1:18:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it not your own intrinsic innocence?\NThat is listening
Dialogue: 0,1:18:32.29,1:18:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,is very second.\NUnderstanding, listening,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:41.76,1:18:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,believing, incorporating\Nin faith and trust
Dialogue: 0,1:18:46.79,1:18:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that that which is being spoken is the truth.\NEven if you disbelieve it
Dialogue: 0,1:18:52.71,1:18:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,then you reject it\Nfrom some opposing program.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:58.18,1:19:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And where did you get the opposing program?\NYou bought that out of your innocence, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:05.08,1:19:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you disagree violently\Nwith what I say
Dialogue: 0,1:19:09.08,1:19:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,what's disagreeing with that is a program.\NThat's your own innocence you bought.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:13.08,1:19:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So your innocence is unsullied\Nwhether you agree, whether you disagree.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:17.08,1:19:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It makes no difference.\NThe truth of that which you are
Dialogue: 0,1:19:21.14,1:19:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is totally unchanged.\NThe truth of that which you are
Dialogue: 0,1:19:25.24,1:19:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is unchanged by the experiences\Nthat go through consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:29.24,1:19:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore the realization\Nthat that is its nature
Dialogue: 0,1:19:33.65,1:19:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that that is the nature of what you are\Nof what we all are
Dialogue: 0,1:19:39.19,1:19:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the nature of what we all are\Nis totally unchanged.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:43.51,1:19:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It is exactly that which we have always been\Nand always will be
Dialogue: 0,1:19:47.51,1:19:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,that that innocence is\Nunassailable
Dialogue: 0,1:19:52.02,1:19:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and not be defended.\NIt is what it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:58.80,1:20:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The undoing of all that it is not\Nallows one to experience
Dialogue: 0,1:20:02.80,1:20:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the truth of that which it is.\NAnd that is the purpose
Dialogue: 0,1:20:07.73,1:20:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,of all spiritual work\Nis the removal of that which we are not.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:11.73,1:20:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So it is the removal\Nof the clouds from the sky
Dialogue: 0,1:20:15.83,1:20:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we can experience the sun\Nalways shining.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:21.24,1:20:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,In the proposition we were testing\Nwith kinesiology
Dialogue: 0,1:20:25.24,1:20:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,what we were really asking was\Ndoes the removal of the clouds
Dialogue: 0,1:20:29.40,1:20:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,cause the sun to shine?\NDoes the removal of the clouds
Dialogue: 0,1:20:34.26,1:20:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,cause the sun to shine?\NOr is the sun always shining
Dialogue: 0,1:20:38.55,1:20:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and when we remove the clouds\Nwe are aware that it is always there?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:42.55,1:20:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That's really comparably\Nthe metaphor of what we were asking.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:46.55,1:20:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The seeing of this\Nentire way of holding clouds
Dialogue: 0,1:20:53.75,1:20:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and things then\Nreveals to us
Dialogue: 0,1:20:57.75,1:21:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and after this lecture\Nthings will begin to unfold
Dialogue: 0,1:21:01.94,1:21:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,because the mind is always looking\Nthere is that within us
Dialogue: 0,1:21:05.94,1:21:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,which is self-healing.\NIt is always looking for that
Dialogue: 0,1:21:09.94,1:21:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,means, those tools\Nthe ways of healing ourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:13.94,1:21:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it begins to dawn on us\Nthat there are ways now
Dialogue: 0,1:21:17.94,1:21:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,of holding things\Nthat will bring about a healing
Dialogue: 0,1:21:22.26,1:21:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that will come out of merely the way\Nof holding it.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:28.63,1:21:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The healing of many of these things then\Nis that you are holding
Dialogue: 0,1:21:34.13,1:21:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,from the lovingness\Nfrom the truth of that which you are
Dialogue: 0,1:21:38.13,1:21:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that which you are not\Nbut you are holding it
Dialogue: 0,1:21:42.13,1:21:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,from that which is greater\Nrather than from that which is lesser.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:46.26,1:21:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,When we are identifying with\Nthat which is lesser
Dialogue: 0,1:21:50.26,1:21:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,we can't look at it\Nbecause we think I am that
Dialogue: 0,1:21:54.26,1:21:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the false identification\Nwith the small self.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:58.26,1:22:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I cannot look at that within myself.\NIf our motivation
Dialogue: 0,1:22:03.00,1:22:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,if our intention is\Nthe healing within ourself
Dialogue: 0,1:22:07.00,1:22:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and when we do it within ourself\Nwe do it within everyone
Dialogue: 0,1:22:11.64,1:22:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,because we are the world\Nwe are everyone.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:15.89,1:22:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole implication\Nof the holographic conceptualization
Dialogue: 0,1:22:20.92,1:22:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is that it reveals\Nthat you are everyone
Dialogue: 0,1:22:24.92,1:22:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that your consciousness is all that is.\NSo as we heal
Dialogue: 0,1:22:28.92,1:22:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,that within ourself\Nwe heal it within the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:33.01,1:22:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people get into a conflict\Nabout myself
Dialogue: 0,1:22:37.01,1:22:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and or the world.\NThat which is myself is not different
Dialogue: 0,1:22:41.88,1:22:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,than that which is the world.\NWhen I heal it within myself
Dialogue: 0,1:22:46.29,1:22:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,then I heal it for everyone.\NAs each of us heals these things within ourself
Dialogue: 0,1:22:50.29,1:22:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,we raise the consciousness of the world.\NEveryone benefits.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:54.29,1:22:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So when we heal ourself\Nit's a win-win situation
Dialogue: 0,1:22:58.29,1:23:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,because out of that lovingness\Nto perfect the awareness of that
Dialogue: 0,1:23:02.29,1:23:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,which we are\Nthen comes the power.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:06.58,1:23:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Empowerment.\NSo the intention coming from this level
Dialogue: 0,1:23:10.58,1:23:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,empowers the person\Nto heal that within oneself
Dialogue: 0,1:23:14.58,1:23:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,which needs to be healed.\NIt's coming out of the way
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.93,1:23:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that it's being looked at.\NIt's coming out of the way it's being held.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:23.96,1:23:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of that we begin to see\Nthat whatever we were
Dialogue: 0,1:23:28.02,1:23:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,in the past was necessary\Nfor us at that moment.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:32.12,1:23:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It is out of the desire\Nfor happiness.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:36.92,1:23:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It is out of the love of life\Nthat all of it came. Did it not?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:41.62,1:23:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's say, angriness.\NWhat is the angriness coming out of?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:45.62,1:23:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the angriness coming out of?\NThe angriness
Dialogue: 0,1:23:50.13,1:23:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,is coming out of your love for life.\NIs it not? And the thought
Dialogue: 0,1:23:54.13,1:23:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that someone is going to impair it in some way.\NSo the way to get out of the guilt
Dialogue: 0,1:23:58.13,1:24:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,about that\Nis to look and see that underlying it all
Dialogue: 0,1:24:02.13,1:24:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,is that innocent,\Nnaive love for life
Dialogue: 0,1:24:06.13,1:24:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the thought that\Nthis is blocking my happiness.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:10.13,1:24:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,All the negative feelings\Nare coming out of the thought
Dialogue: 0,1:24:14.20,1:24:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that my happiness is out there\Nand something is interfering with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:19.22,1:24:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I always say, and I don't know whether it's true or not\NI invite everybody to dial this in
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.22,1:24:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and test their kinesiology\Nthat you can't really love unless you've hated.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:27.22,1:24:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't care enough\Nabout life to hate somebody
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.22,1:24:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,who you feel is threatening life itself\Nthen you will never rise
Dialogue: 0,1:24:35.22,1:24:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to the level of loving it.\NIf you're in apathy
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.22,1:24:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,if you don't care enough about life\Nyou wouldn't even get angry, would you?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:43.22,1:24:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it's hopeless.\NIt's so sad that you can't even get involved in it.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:47.22,1:24:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Kitty Genovese or whatever it was\Npeople just withdrew from the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:51.22,1:24:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,There wasn't the commitment of life\Nenough to even be angry about it
Dialogue: 0,1:24:55.22,1:24:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to even do anything about it.\NEverybody went into apathy.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:59.22,1:25:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you look back\Nat the things that you condemn within yourself
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.72,1:25:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,the way you heal it, as you say\Nin the becoming awareness
Dialogue: 0,1:25:09.43,1:25:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,of that which I am\Nit was necessary for me to experience that then.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:13.43,1:25:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But at that time\Nthat's what I needed.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:17.75,1:25:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,At that time, that's what had to be with me\Nbecause who I was at the time
Dialogue: 0,1:25:21.75,1:25:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,thought that that was the best thing to do.\NAnd doesn't the mind in its innocence
Dialogue: 0,1:25:25.75,1:25:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,always choose\Nthat which it thinks is the best thing to do?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:29.75,1:25:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Does your mind ever do anything else?\NIt always chooses what it thinks at the moment
Dialogue: 0,1:25:33.84,1:25:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,is the best decision, does it not?\NEven if it gets into an impulse
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.94,1:25:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that it hates itself for later\Nit still makes the decision
Dialogue: 0,1:25:41.94,1:25:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that for me at this time\Nthe best thing to do is to throw the brick
Dialogue: 0,1:25:45.94,1:25:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,through the son of a bitch's window.\NLater I may feel guilty about that
Dialogue: 0,1:25:49.94,1:25:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,but at that moment the feeling\Nthat I must express my aliveness
Dialogue: 0,1:25:53.94,1:25:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,in that form that is meaningful to me\Nmay well be necessary.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:58.07,1:26:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll never forget the first time\NI met a guy coming in
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.58,1:26:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,out of the parking lot\Nand I was always a very
Dialogue: 0,1:26:06.58,1:26:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess what you call people pleaser, right?\NAnd so we got into conflict
Dialogue: 0,1:26:10.58,1:26:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,about who had the driveway\Nand so I gave him the finger.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:14.58,1:26:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Well I'll tell you\NI was ecstatically happy. I had never done that before
Dialogue: 0,1:26:18.58,1:26:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,in my life. I never told somebody\Nto go you know where. Never did it.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:22.58,1:26:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I was fifty something\Nyears old before I finally did that.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:26.58,1:26:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was so pleased with myself\Nyou see, that I'd gotten up to that
Dialogue: 0,1:26:30.58,1:26:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, not out of hopelessness\Nnot out of fear
Dialogue: 0,1:26:34.58,1:26:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,not out of fear that you won't be a\Nspiritual person if you do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:38.58,1:26:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't be a spiritual person man\Nif you tell somebody where to go.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:42.58,1:26:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But I got such a, I got hysterical\Nlaughing over it you know. First I told him where to go
Dialogue: 0,1:26:46.58,1:26:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and then I broke down and I almost went off the\Nroad laughing at the whole thing
Dialogue: 0,1:26:50.58,1:26:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,because it was such fun. And then I went\Naround doing that a little while because I was getting off on it
Dialogue: 0,1:26:54.58,1:26:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and then finally gave up on it but\Nit was really fun to do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:58.58,1:27:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You know where to go. You can go there.\NHey, here, look. It was really
Dialogue: 0,1:27:02.58,1:27:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,great fun.\NNecessary, necessary to know that I
Dialogue: 0,1:27:07.00,1:27:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,could do that. Necessary that I could hold\Nit that way. That I could
Dialogue: 0,1:27:11.00,1:27:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,experience it in a self-healing way.\NSee? And not go into guilt
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.00,1:27:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,about it and self-condemnation.\NSo, that which we've been
Dialogue: 0,1:27:19.54,1:27:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,was necessary in the evolution of\Nour becoming that which we are
Dialogue: 0,1:27:23.54,1:27:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,becoming aware of. All of that\Nis necessary. For the
Dialogue: 0,1:27:27.76,1:27:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,addicted person then, in\Nthe interest of his own consciousness growth
Dialogue: 0,1:27:31.76,1:27:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,it is absolutely essential\Nand it is absolutely necessary
Dialogue: 0,1:27:35.76,1:27:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,in this lifetime, at this time\Nthat this be what
Dialogue: 0,1:27:39.76,1:27:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the person is experiencing.\NAbsolutely critical to their
Dialogue: 0,1:27:43.76,1:27:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,life. That confrontation\Nwith the absoluteness
Dialogue: 0,1:27:47.83,1:27:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,of facing the truth about yourself or\Ndying. And that's what it takes.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:51.83,1:27:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what it takes a lot of us.\NThat's what it took me. It was in the
Dialogue: 0,1:27:55.83,1:27:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,teeth of death itself\Nthat the transformation took place.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:59.83,1:28:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It took all of it. It took all of it\Nto bring about that surrender.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:03.83,1:28:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And some people\Nknow the ego is not so strong.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:08.79,1:28:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't take that severity, that\Ndegree. In the old days in the
Dialogue: 0,1:28:12.79,1:28:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,AA, it was thought that everybody had to reach\Nthe pits of hell before they
Dialogue: 0,1:28:16.79,1:28:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,gave up. And of course we know\Nthat is not true.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:20.79,1:28:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It is not at all true that anybody\Ncan learn from this education.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:24.85,1:28:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And from the education, from\Nthis awareness itself, it raises the
Dialogue: 0,1:28:28.85,1:28:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,bottom so that people don't have to go\Nto this level called destruction
Dialogue: 0,1:28:32.85,1:28:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,before they finally surrender.\NOkay, we've got time for
Dialogue: 0,1:28:37.20,1:28:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,a few minutes for questions and answers.\NSo, anything that you want to
Dialogue: 0,1:28:41.20,1:28:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,discuss or you'd like to have elaborated,\Nyou can just
Dialogue: 0,1:28:45.20,1:28:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,bring it up. Yes, please.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:55.38,1:29:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy field,\Nand I didn't talk much about that, so I'm glad
Dialogue: 0,1:29:00.69,1:29:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you brought it up.\NThe question was, why do we
Dialogue: 0,1:29:05.36,1:29:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,have to keep moving up and down in the field?\NAnd it is something that
Dialogue: 0,1:29:09.72,1:29:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,we didn't discuss before, and I'm glad you\Nsort of brought it up. That the energy
Dialogue: 0,1:29:13.72,1:29:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,field comes about as a result of\None's commitment. In other words,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:17.72,1:29:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I have the power\Nto create a certain energy field
Dialogue: 0,1:29:21.72,1:29:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,by my free will,\Nby my agreement, by my assent,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:25.72,1:29:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,by the alignment of my goals,\Nmy purpose, my intention.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.42,1:29:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, that sets the power of the field.\NNow, within that,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:34.87,1:29:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,there may be daily variations\Nlike the stock market. There is
Dialogue: 0,1:29:38.87,1:29:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,jiggles up and down. So a person who is\Ncommitted to lovingness
Dialogue: 0,1:29:42.87,1:29:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,may still experience these feelings.\NAnd feelings, as you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:46.87,1:29:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,move very rapidly. Sometimes\Nchange half a dozen times without
Dialogue: 0,1:29:50.87,1:29:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,a second, those fleeting\Nfluctuations. So this is sort of
Dialogue: 0,1:29:54.87,1:29:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,scintillating, changing. Those\Nwho see auras, especially auras
Dialogue: 0,1:29:58.87,1:30:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,in color, see that scintillation\Nof the constant shifting of the emotional fields.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:02.87,1:30:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,But the person's commitment\Nhasn't changed. Their commitment
Dialogue: 0,1:30:07.09,1:30:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,hasn't changed.\NYou are the same person before and after
Dialogue: 0,1:30:11.09,1:30:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the experience. The person\Nwho changes their commitment, that is a different story.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:15.09,1:30:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But your commitment\Nis the same. So you can be committed
Dialogue: 0,1:30:19.19,1:30:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to a loving relationship\Nand suddenly get mad as the
Dialogue: 0,1:30:23.19,1:30:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,devil at them. Suddenly angry\Nat them and that will flare up
Dialogue: 0,1:30:27.19,1:30:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,from the solar plexus. But that\Ndoesn't change your intention.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:31.19,1:30:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't change your commitment.\NYou can be mad at your boss. That doesn't mean you're quitting
Dialogue: 0,1:30:35.19,1:30:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,today. It just means that you're angry at him today.\NYour commitment to do a good job
Dialogue: 0,1:30:39.19,1:30:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and your commitment to work for this company or your\Ncommitment to your career
Dialogue: 0,1:30:43.19,1:30:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,is going to remain the same.\NSome days you may be enthusiastic about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:47.19,1:30:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Some days you may feel it's hopeless.\NI'll never become a whatever.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:51.19,1:30:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can fluctuate in the\Nscintillating emotionality
Dialogue: 0,1:30:56.05,1:31:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,but the commitment\Nremains the same. The commitment
Dialogue: 0,1:31:00.05,1:31:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,remains the same and therefore your power\Nis in the field of the commitment
Dialogue: 0,1:31:04.05,1:31:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's the commitment that holds the power.\NIt's the commitment
Dialogue: 0,1:31:08.12,1:31:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that has set the energy field.\NThe energy field, see let's
Dialogue: 0,1:31:12.24,1:31:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,say one time at the\Nbill a girl said to me, after hearing your lecture she said
Dialogue: 0,1:31:16.24,1:31:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I really feel bad about my\Nresentments now. And I said, well that's
Dialogue: 0,1:31:20.24,1:31:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,easy to get rid of. You can get rid of\Nthat very easily. Just hate the son of a
Dialogue: 0,1:31:24.24,1:31:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,bitch. I mean if you set this as\Nyour goal then
Dialogue: 0,1:31:28.24,1:31:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,resentments won't make you feel guilty.\NIf you set this as
Dialogue: 0,1:31:33.11,1:31:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the goal then\Nso whatever level we set for ourself
Dialogue: 0,1:31:37.11,1:31:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,what becomes unacceptable\Nto us is that which is below it.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:41.11,1:31:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,In a group where\Nangriness is okay
Dialogue: 0,1:31:45.43,1:31:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,then you don't feel upset about resentments.\NBut when you move up to a commitment
Dialogue: 0,1:31:49.43,1:31:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,to loving this, now resentments\Nbecome painful. And
Dialogue: 0,1:31:53.43,1:31:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,the desire is to be rid of that resentment\Nas quickly as possible.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:57.43,1:32:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people have utilized\Nthis intuitively
Dialogue: 0,1:32:01.68,1:32:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,in grand\Nsocial demonstrations.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:05.68,1:32:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you want to remember how to utilize\Nthese energy fields positively
Dialogue: 0,1:32:09.68,1:32:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,just remember\Nthe social demonstration of the black
Dialogue: 0,1:32:13.68,1:32:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,people in the United States.\NIn my lifetime I watched them move
Dialogue: 0,1:32:17.68,1:32:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,from the bottom of the box all the way to the top.\NWhen I was young
Dialogue: 0,1:32:22.07,1:32:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,they all lived at the back of the bus. Black people\Nbelonged at the back of the bus.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:26.07,1:32:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And they were into hopelessness and apathy.\NAnd that hopelessness and apathy
Dialogue: 0,1:32:30.07,1:32:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,was represented in the physical\Nattitude and the way they
Dialogue: 0,1:32:34.07,1:32:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,walked and the way they shuffled\Nin that hopeless apathy
Dialogue: 0,1:32:38.07,1:32:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,because nothing was ever going to get better.\NIt became a caricature
Dialogue: 0,1:32:42.07,1:32:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,a stereotype on the stage\Nof that walk
Dialogue: 0,1:32:46.07,1:32:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,of hopelessness and apathy\Nand the grief over
Dialogue: 0,1:32:50.07,1:32:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the grief over\Nhow men express
Dialogue: 0,1:32:54.10,1:32:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,primarily by the women\Nover the hopelessness of the situation
Dialogue: 0,1:32:58.10,1:33:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,over the cost, over the realization\Nthat her children would never have a chance
Dialogue: 0,1:33:02.10,1:33:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,in this world. All of this\Ncontrolled by the tremendous fear
Dialogue: 0,1:33:06.58,1:33:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,the fear of the lynch mob. If the black man\Nprotested he got hung from the
Dialogue: 0,1:33:10.58,1:33:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,nearest tree. And so the intimidation\Nand the terror, progressive
Dialogue: 0,1:33:14.58,1:33:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,systematized terrorization.\NThen along came television
Dialogue: 0,1:33:19.00,1:33:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and the submerged\Npart of the world, the third world
Dialogue: 0,1:33:23.00,1:33:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the black people in America began\Nto see, began to see
Dialogue: 0,1:33:27.00,1:33:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,through television that which the rest\Nof the world has. They began to see
Dialogue: 0,1:33:31.00,1:33:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,what other people have. The kind of houses\Nthey lived in and the way they
Dialogue: 0,1:33:35.00,1:33:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the style, the lifestyle, etc.\NOut of that desiringness
Dialogue: 0,1:33:39.51,1:33:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and wantingness came anger and the frustration\Nof that. And then we saw
Dialogue: 0,1:33:43.51,1:33:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the arriving of black pride\Nthe pride in one's blackness
Dialogue: 0,1:33:47.51,1:33:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,now. No longer the shame\Nthe self-effacement
Dialogue: 0,1:33:51.51,1:33:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the fear about it\Nwe saw the black anger and the
Dialogue: 0,1:33:55.51,1:33:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,angerness. The energy\Nthe upside of that angerness
Dialogue: 0,1:33:59.51,1:34:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,was then\Nthrough the intuition, through the inspiration
Dialogue: 0,1:34:03.54,1:34:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,of some of their great leaders\Nled into black pride. Out of the anger
Dialogue: 0,1:34:07.54,1:34:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,then the energy of the anger\Nis built into black pride.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:11.54,1:34:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,There was some expression of the downside\Nsome of the teenagers, the expression of the
Dialogue: 0,1:34:15.54,1:34:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,angerness in the form of anger\Nand destructiveness as
Dialogue: 0,1:34:19.54,1:34:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,happened also in pride.\NBut a great, enough of that energy
Dialogue: 0,1:34:23.64,1:34:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,was utilized in a positive way.\NAnd so out of the pride you saw the courage
Dialogue: 0,1:34:27.64,1:34:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to face and cope with\Nwhat are the problems that have to be handled
Dialogue: 0,1:34:31.64,1:34:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,here to change our way of life.\NAnd there you saw
Dialogue: 0,1:34:35.64,1:34:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the legal battles and you saw\Nthe bringing in
Dialogue: 0,1:34:39.64,1:34:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,of the courts and of social conscience\Nand the enlistment
Dialogue: 0,1:34:43.64,1:34:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,of the energy and the power\Nof the white population
Dialogue: 0,1:34:47.64,1:34:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,as they become inspired to\Na higher view of man.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:51.64,1:34:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So we saw them move through courage\Nup through
Dialogue: 0,1:34:55.64,1:34:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the acceptance of that which needs to be\Nhandled and needs to be done
Dialogue: 0,1:34:59.64,1:35:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and the acceptance of equality on the part of\Nwhite people who had never even thought of it in their
Dialogue: 0,1:35:03.64,1:35:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,lifetime now began to think\Nthat perhaps black people are the same
Dialogue: 0,1:35:07.64,1:35:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,equal to us and the emergence\Nof love. And you saw the success
Dialogue: 0,1:35:11.64,1:35:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,of many social movements and of course\Nthe black people who were now once at the back of the bus
Dialogue: 0,1:35:15.64,1:35:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,in my lifetime are now mayors of cities\Nand great entertainers and millionaires
Dialogue: 0,1:35:19.64,1:35:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and leaders of industry\Nand senators and congressmen
Dialogue: 0,1:35:23.64,1:35:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and all the rest. So not all\Nof their population but certainly a size
Dialogue: 0,1:35:27.64,1:35:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,of Lamont has demonstrated\Nhow to utilize
Dialogue: 0,1:35:31.64,1:35:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,these levels of consciousness.\NHow to use the upside. How to use
Dialogue: 0,1:35:35.64,1:35:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy of it. How to\Nutilize the energy of the anger and the
Dialogue: 0,1:35:39.64,1:35:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,indignation to mobilize\Nsocial forces to bring
Dialogue: 0,1:35:43.64,1:35:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,about changes in the senate, in the congress,\Nin the governors, in the
Dialogue: 0,1:35:47.86,1:35:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,laws on the municipal\Nstate federal level.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:51.86,1:35:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,How to enlist the moral support\Nof the country. You know
Dialogue: 0,1:35:55.86,1:35:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,great power coming out of that\Ninspiration, that dedication
Dialogue: 0,1:35:59.86,1:36:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,to a cause that is greater than one's self.\NThe dedication to a cause
Dialogue: 0,1:36:03.86,1:36:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,that is greater than one's self\Nthen allowed the power
Dialogue: 0,1:36:07.86,1:36:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,to express itself in that social\Ntransition. In powerful
Dialogue: 0,1:36:11.86,1:36:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,social changes. Yes?\NThat's a very good point.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:30.53,1:36:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That when you fall below\Nthat which you are committed to, what you run into
Dialogue: 0,1:36:34.53,1:36:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,is pain. And therefore it is\Nself-educating. You know that
Dialogue: 0,1:36:38.53,1:36:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,it's out because it doesn't feel right anymore.\NSee when you're dedicated
Dialogue: 0,1:36:42.53,1:36:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to hating this, you're dedicated to\Nhating this, everything below it is
Dialogue: 0,1:36:46.53,1:36:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,painful. When you're dedicated to\Npride let's say.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:50.53,1:36:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're dedicated to pride then fear\Nis no longer acceptable. And that's
Dialogue: 0,1:36:54.53,1:36:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,part of the passages of the adolescent\Nboy. It's part of the passages
Dialogue: 0,1:36:58.53,1:37:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,of becoming\Nthe United States Marine Corps let's say.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:02.53,1:37:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The expression\Nor the overt acknowledgement
Dialogue: 0,1:37:06.53,1:37:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,of this is no longer acceptable\Nbecause now what you're committed to
Dialogue: 0,1:37:10.53,1:37:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,is pride. They'll say brace up boy.\NBrace up boy.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:14.53,1:37:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are only bullets.\NThey'll tear your guts to pieces.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:18.53,1:37:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are only bullets.\NI mean they'll only go through you.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:22.53,1:37:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What's to be afraid of?\NAnd so
Dialogue: 0,1:37:26.53,1:37:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and then when I was in the Navy I was on a\Nminesweeper and of course we swept
Dialogue: 0,1:37:30.53,1:37:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,mines in the East China Sea so\Nminesweepers were blowing up all over
Dialogue: 0,1:37:34.53,1:37:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,so it wasn't you were going to get bullets\Nyou were going to just get blown up.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:38.53,1:37:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So we all went into neutral.\NWe all went into
Dialogue: 0,1:37:42.53,1:37:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,if you blow up you blow up and if you don't\Nyou don't.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:46.63,1:37:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,When we went out to sweep mines you\Nbattened all the hatches and you had to take your
Dialogue: 0,1:37:50.63,1:37:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,stuff, whatever stuff you needed for the day\Nfrom below you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:54.63,1:37:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they battened the hatches nobody was allowed to be\Nbelow hatches because if you blew up
Dialogue: 0,1:37:58.63,1:38:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the compression there would like, I don't want you to go\Ninto an anatomical description but
Dialogue: 0,1:38:02.63,1:38:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,you stayed above decks.\NBut that was the way it was handled.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:07.08,1:38:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It was handled in\Nso fatalism we might add that as a
Dialogue: 0,1:38:11.33,1:38:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,neat way of neutral.\NThe fatalist then is a good expression
Dialogue: 0,1:38:15.33,1:38:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,of that energy field.\NIf you blow up you blow up and if you don't you don't.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:19.33,1:38:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And you know what difference does it make?\NI mean when you go
Dialogue: 0,1:38:23.33,1:38:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,so that's the fatalistic\Nand many men in our
Dialogue: 0,1:38:27.33,1:38:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,society have developed that\Nyou know as a result of their experiences in the war
Dialogue: 0,1:38:31.33,1:38:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,it was really the only way you could handle it.\NI mean you can't walk around in a panic all day long
Dialogue: 0,1:38:35.33,1:38:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's socially unacceptable.\NThere's nothing to be angry about.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:39.33,1:38:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't be into apathy\NI'll tell you that.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:43.56,1:38:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And lovingness just doesn't seem\Nthe lovingness is the
Dialogue: 0,1:38:47.56,1:38:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,bonding that goes on between the men\Nand so there are those profound
Dialogue: 0,1:38:51.56,1:38:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,bonds of love which last\Nmany years. This last year I
Dialogue: 0,1:38:55.56,1:38:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,happened to get together with a friend I hadn't\Nseen in 40 years who was
Dialogue: 0,1:38:59.56,1:39:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,with me in the navy back in\N1945.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:03.56,1:39:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But 40 years later that\Ncommitment, that bonding of love
Dialogue: 0,1:39:07.56,1:39:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,had not changed when I\Nsaw him or loved him just as much
Dialogue: 0,1:39:11.56,1:39:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,as I always had as though 40 years had\Nnever gone by. So that
Dialogue: 0,1:39:15.78,1:39:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,bonding and that love. So that was the strength\Nthen, the strength
Dialogue: 0,1:39:19.78,1:39:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,out of which that strength is coming\Nto handle the threat to life
Dialogue: 0,1:39:23.78,1:39:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,itself on its most dramatic\Nexpression from moment to moment.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:27.78,1:39:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So all these things have their\Npositive
Dialogue: 0,1:39:31.84,1:39:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,way of holding them positively.\NIt's certainly better to be detached
Dialogue: 0,1:39:37.84,1:39:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,certainly better to be into fatalism\Nthan to be in a state of panic
Dialogue: 0,1:39:41.84,1:39:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,which is paralyzing you.\NBecause in neutrality we can function
Dialogue: 0,1:39:45.84,1:39:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and we all do.\N...
Dialogue: 0,1:39:54.77,1:39:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and knowing that it's there\Nand it's attainable
Dialogue: 0,1:39:59.19,1:40:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and yet having setbacks\Nand conscious
Dialogue: 0,1:40:05.52,1:40:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,awareness and working of\Nwithin my mind
Dialogue: 0,1:40:09.52,1:40:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the things I need to do to come back\Nto that higher level.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:13.52,1:40:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The desire to return to that\Nlevel. What? What? Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:20.02,1:40:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Am I\Na creature of nature and
Dialogue: 0,1:40:24.05,1:40:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I go back there automatically?\NCan I use my left brain to bring myself
Dialogue: 0,1:40:28.05,1:40:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,back there? Can I apply\Nlogic to
Dialogue: 0,1:40:33.40,1:40:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the attainment of ecstasy?\NWhat we've been talking about today is
Dialogue: 0,1:40:39.32,1:40:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,is a balance between\Nleft and right brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:43.76,1:40:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Being, having grown up as a left\Nbrain person, then having become
Dialogue: 0,1:40:47.76,1:40:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,excessively a right brain person\Nand then coming back to balance.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:51.76,1:40:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What we try to do is\Nexpress all of this in a balanced way
Dialogue: 0,1:40:55.76,1:40:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,because the left brain\Nso often will take
Dialogue: 0,1:40:59.76,1:41:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the position that the right\Nbrain way of viewing things
Dialogue: 0,1:41:03.76,1:41:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,is illogical.\NAnd so by the research we've been
Dialogue: 0,1:41:07.76,1:41:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,doing you see that\Nthe truth is approachable equally from
Dialogue: 0,1:41:11.76,1:41:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,either left or right brain.\NOnce the left brain
Dialogue: 0,1:41:15.76,1:41:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,begins all of this, it now no longer\Nhas any objection. It is logical,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:19.76,1:41:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,it's scientifically\Ndemonstrable, but
Dialogue: 0,1:41:23.92,1:41:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,they're generally, you can test them with\Nkinesiology, you can get the same,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:27.92,1:41:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you can test each other with kinesiology, you can just say\Nyou know, if I hold in mind pride
Dialogue: 0,1:41:31.92,1:41:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is it over 150, or 160, or\N170, or 170, about 175 a Sunday
Dialogue: 0,1:41:35.92,1:41:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,a week? It is not above 175.\NSo you can set these and verify
Dialogue: 0,1:41:39.92,1:41:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,them experientially, the truth of this\Nwithin yourself. That removes
Dialogue: 0,1:41:43.92,1:41:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the objections of the left brain.\NTo the fact that this is not logical.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:47.92,1:41:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,See?\NNobody was a more skeptical left brain person
Dialogue: 0,1:41:51.92,1:41:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,than myself. I didn't believe\Nany of this. You see the mystic
Dialogue: 0,1:41:57.49,1:42:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,is not, the wisdom of the mystic\Nis not accessible to the left brain
Dialogue: 0,1:42:01.49,1:42:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,person. Because the mystic\Nexperiences it, but he can't
Dialogue: 0,1:42:06.74,1:42:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,communicate it to a left brain person\Nin any way that's useful to the left brain person.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:10.74,1:42:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore\Nwhat we tried to do is translate
Dialogue: 0,1:42:15.89,1:42:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,it into language.\NBecause the truth is the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:19.89,1:42:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,If the truth is true, then it's true on all levels.\NAnd it should be as understandable from
Dialogue: 0,1:42:23.89,1:42:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,one side as the other.\NDeath being zero, that's rather obvious, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:34.32,1:42:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NIf you start with the proposition
Dialogue: 0,1:42:38.32,1:42:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that death is zero,\Nthen you can use like kinesiology
Dialogue: 0,1:42:42.32,1:42:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that we use today. You can say if death is zero\Nthen what is the relative energy fueled
Dialogue: 0,1:42:46.32,1:42:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,of apathy?\NYou can calibrate this for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:50.32,1:42:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Then what is the relative energy fueled\Nof desire? Then what is the relative
Dialogue: 0,1:42:54.32,1:42:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,energy fueled of anger? It's very simple.\NYou say, I'm holding anger
Dialogue: 0,1:42:58.32,1:43:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,in mind. Is that over 70?\NIs that over 80? Is that over 90?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:02.32,1:43:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that over 100? Is that over 120?\NIs that over 140? Is that over 150?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:06.32,1:43:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And at 150 your body will say\Nthat's its relative strength
Dialogue: 0,1:43:10.32,1:43:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,as compared.\NAnd if you keep doing that all the way up,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:14.32,1:43:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll end up with the same numbers that I have.\NBecause we've verified this
Dialogue: 0,1:43:18.32,1:43:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,with a number of people.\NIf you use those energy fuels, those are about the kind of
Dialogue: 0,1:43:23.35,1:43:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,numbers that you will come up with.\NAnd what is the value of it?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:27.35,1:43:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The value of it is mind-boggling.\NFor those who can see,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:31.35,1:43:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,it is mind-boggling, the implications\Nof these numbers
Dialogue: 0,1:43:35.35,1:43:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and the reversities of these\Nenergy fuels.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:39.35,1:43:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It gives you a way to hold\Nall of human experience now
Dialogue: 0,1:43:43.35,1:43:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,from a way that becomes self-healing\Nthrough that understanding.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:47.35,1:43:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is the whole purpose of today's\Ntalk.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:51.35,1:43:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The talk is really about self-healing\Nand of course self-healing
Dialogue: 0,1:43:55.35,1:43:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,explicitly as it applies to the\Naddictions, but we're talking about
Dialogue: 0,1:43:59.35,1:44:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the basic principles\Nof self-healing in general.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:03.35,1:44:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What we say today really applies\Nto everyone and
Dialogue: 0,1:44:07.35,1:44:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,of course we related it specifically\Nto the addictions.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:11.35,1:44:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What we're talking about is the nature of consciousness\Nitself, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:15.35,1:44:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,aside from the addictions,\Nbut with its special
Dialogue: 0,1:44:19.44,1:44:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,application to the\Naddictions themselves.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:23.92,1:44:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it you'd be willing to give up\Nif really asked for all?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:29.88,1:44:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,For what would you give up\Nall of it? For what would you say
Dialogue: 0,1:44:34.58,1:44:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,take it?\NWhat are you willing to die for? What are you willing
Dialogue: 0,1:44:40.66,1:44:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,to commit to?\NWhat are the limitations
Dialogue: 0,1:44:44.98,1:44:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and the considerations?\NWhen people get sober, we ask them to make
Dialogue: 0,1:44:50.96,1:44:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the same commitment as\Nthey did before.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:55.44,1:44:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And in the fifth chapter\Nin the book Alcoholics Anonymous, it says
Dialogue: 0,1:44:59.44,1:45:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that those\Nwho succeeded in getting sober
Dialogue: 0,1:45:04.31,1:45:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,were those who did not\Ndraw any line in how far they were willing to go.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:08.31,1:45:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever was needed,\Nthey were willing to go the whole way
Dialogue: 0,1:45:12.31,1:45:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,for whatever was needed.\NThat they did not hold back.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:16.76,1:45:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,That sobriety came only to those who were willing\Nto go the whole way.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:21.17,1:45:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever was asked, the willingness to go\Nthe whole route. And it was out of that
Dialogue: 0,1:45:25.17,1:45:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that sobriety arose.\NThe willingness to go the whole way.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:29.17,1:45:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,To hold back nothing.\NEven if life itself is asked.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:33.17,1:45:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,With that spiritual awareness\Nthen, there comes
Dialogue: 0,1:45:38.74,1:45:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,an unlimitedness to what one is\Nwilling to let go of
Dialogue: 0,1:45:42.74,1:45:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,in the name of that\Nintention, in the name of that goal.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:46.87,1:45:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Even life itself.\NOkay, so
Dialogue: 0,1:45:54.84,1:45:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,here's Leo. Thanks Leo\Nfor this opportunity to be here today.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:59.12,1:46:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we would like to thank\NDave Hawkins. I'd like to give a hand.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:03.48,1:46:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps a few of you would\Nwant to say a few words of thanks.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:13.27,1:46:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't here for the whole day\Nso I can't really comment. I know
Dialogue: 0,1:46:17.27,1:46:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the parts that I heard I was very much\Nimpressed with and very much
Dialogue: 0,1:46:21.27,1:46:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,enlightened and moved by.\NWould anyone want to
Dialogue: 0,1:46:25.27,1:46:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,say a few words\Nof what they got out of today or something like that?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:29.27,1:46:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NIt's like hearing it
Dialogue: 0,1:46:38.23,1:46:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,explained to me. Somehow giving it some\Nunderstanding.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:42.42,1:46:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I've just been grateful all day that you do this for me.\NWell, I forgot
Dialogue: 0,1:46:47.48,1:46:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to say today, and I usually do, that\Nyou won't hear anything today that you don't
Dialogue: 0,1:46:51.48,1:46:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,already know. You're just not\Nconscious that you know it. And therefore,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:55.48,1:46:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,it's an intense feeling of familiarity.\NAs we talk about this, it's like
Dialogue: 0,1:46:59.48,1:47:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I always knew that. Part of me\Nalways knew this, and that part
Dialogue: 0,1:47:03.48,1:47:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,of me that always knew it, but\Nforgot it, brought me here today
Dialogue: 0,1:47:07.48,1:47:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to remind itself\Nof that which is useful
Dialogue: 0,1:47:11.48,1:47:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,in that knowingness.\NSimple exercise.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:18.98,1:47:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's\Nthe source of my joy. The reason I
Dialogue: 0,1:47:23.20,1:47:27.49,Default,,0,0,0,,give these talks here or any place\Nelse is the sheer joy I get
Dialogue: 0,1:47:27.49,1:47:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,out of doing it, frankly.\NThe sheer joy
Dialogue: 0,1:47:31.72,1:47:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,out of just sharing it. That\Nwhich I experience benefit
Dialogue: 0,1:47:35.75,1:47:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,from myself. And\Nthe joy of sharing that
Dialogue: 0,1:47:40.00,1:47:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,with other people. That's the great\Njoy of it. I appreciate how you gave our
Dialogue: 0,1:47:50.69,1:47:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,left brain something to focus on while\Nyou were creating this whole context and energy
Dialogue: 0,1:47:54.69,1:47:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,field with your energy\Nfield and really inducting us into all the
Dialogue: 0,1:47:58.69,1:48:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,information. Great maneuver.\NIt feels terrific.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:02.69,1:48:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. All of it happened\Nas it was, does it not?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:10.72,1:48:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, fine. Thank you very much, Dave. We are truly grateful.\NThanks again, Bill.
